title: terrific 3 bean salad
directions: Rinse all beans.
Place in large glass bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Let sit covered in refrigerator overnight.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in bread pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients, stirring well.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls into hot oil; cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: blt dip
directions: Dice tomatoes, then mix with mayo, sour cream and bacon bits. Serve on crackers.

title: blueberry upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Mix berries and lemon rind and put in pan, distributing evenly.
Cream remaining margarine.
Add granulated sugar and beat until light.
Add egg and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to first mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Spread on berries.
Bake in preheated 375° oven about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, then turn out on serving dish.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt cocoa in skillet with oleo.
Pour into bowl containing flour, sugar and eggs.
Beat until mixed, then add chopped pecans. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and bake in a 300° oven until done, about 45 minutes.
Place marshmallows on top; put in oven until melted.
When cool, frost with chocolate icing.

title: four-minute fudge
directions: In microwavable bowl, stir condensed milk, semi-sweet morsels and vanilla together until well blended.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for four minutes.
Mix in shelled walnuts.
Pour on top of wax paper and shape.
Let sit to harden or place in refrigerator for a quick two hours.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and bake 1 hour at 400° or until done. Cool slightly. Cut thin slice from top of potatoes. Scoop out potatoes and mash. Blend in sour cream, milk, cheese, butter, salt and pepper, beating with electric mixer until fluffy. Spoon mixture into potato shells. Sprinkle with bacon. Put on baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: chipotle mayonnaise
directions: *Chipotle Chiles should be the ones that are canned in adobo sauce and should be finely chopped.

title: salami ribbons
directions: Mix cream cheese and soup mix to spreading consistency. Spread mixture on salami slices.
Stack salami 4 or 5 slices high. Refrigerate.
Slice in bite size sections.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: beef rigatoni bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°; grease 2-quart casserole. In large saucepan, cook rigatoni to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; return to saucepan.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: In saucepan combine sugar, water, cocoa, butter and salt. Bring to a full boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir until blended. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Cool and enjoy!

title: punch to make a gallon
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except ginger ale) in a gallon jug.
Add enough water to make 1 gallon. When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: black walnut strip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add flour. Work in vanilla, water and nuts.
Shape into fingers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (watch to make sure they do not brown too much; check bottom of cookies). When cooled, put powdered sugar on top.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put half of potatoes in greased casserole, layer in ingredients ending with cheese on top.
Pour in enough milk so you can see it down in, but not covering pot.
Bake in preheated 350°
oven 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are well cooked.

title: coconut krinkles
directions: Combine coconut, nuts and cereal in large mixing bowl. Set aside.

title: sauce for hot potato salad
directions: Brown bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Keep for garnish. Add flour to grease and blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over potatoes.
Makes enough for about 5 pounds potatoes.
May be kept in refrigerator and reheated as needed. Also good over beets and beans.

title: cap'n crunch snack
directions: Mix.
Heat sugar and white syrup until it dissolves.
Take off the fire and add the rest.
Pour the cereal in a bowl.
Pour the rest over it hot and mix it all up together.
Cool.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone if necessary.
Crumble toast and cornbread together first, then add the remaining ingredients.
Add chicken broth until mixed thoroughly.
Lightly grease a 10 x 12-inch or 8 x 12-inch pan and cook in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix yeast and 1/2 cup warm water well.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Stir in eggs, cheese and flour.
Knead well.
Let rise until double.
Punch down.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Make 2 or 3 balls.
Shape into loaves.
Place into well-greased pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake 2 large loaves at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or 3 small loaves at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: easy caesar salad
directions: Mash anchovies with a fork in bowl.
Stir in cheese and dressing.
Combine with torn lettuce and croutons.
Serve.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine everything but crispy cereal together. Mix well. Add crispy cereal. Pinch off dough in small amounts. Roll into a ball and place on an un-greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes until lightly brown. Cool. Then, store in air tight container.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses.
Mix with lemon juice, mayonnaise, nuts, garlic and red pepper in mixer.
Make into a ball.
Roll in mixture of chili powder and paprika.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Melt together the margarine and Velveeta cheese.
Pour over carrots in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in jar.
Cover; shake vigorously.
Chill to blend flavors.
Remove garlic, shake again before serving. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: chop suey hot dish
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Add Oriental vegetables, soup and chow mein noodles.
Mix well and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: olde english trifle
directions: Cut the trifle sponges in half and spread with jam, then sandwich together. Arrange in the base of a glass serving dish. Cover with ratafias and sprinkle with sherry. Coat the bananas in lemon juice. Arrange the bananas and cherries on top of the ratafias.
Heat the milk in a medium saucepan until almost boiling.

In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, lemon rind and sugar until pale, then pour on the hot milk, stirring continuously. Return to the saucepan and heat gently, stirring continuously, until the custard thickens enough to coat the back of a wooden spoon.
Do not allow to boil. This takes about 20 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Pour the custard over the trifle and leave until cold.
Whip the cream until stiff and pipe on the top of the trifle and decorate with glace cherries and nuts.

title: mustard pickles(yield: 6 to 8 pints)
directions: Wash vegetables before cutting.
Mix salt and water.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight.
Bring to boiling point and drain in colander.
Add to dressing and cook until vegetables are heated through.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: tomato dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar with screw-top.
Shake thoroughly before using.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Fry hamburger, drain it.
Drain beans and reserve liquid.
Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. If liquid cooks out, add some of reserved bean liquid.
(Add 1 teaspoon of baking soda to help eliminate gas.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel corn
directions: Stir together butter or margarine, brown sugar, salt and syrup.
Bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes on low heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and stir to coat.
Bake in large pan for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Pam or other spray oil into cast frying pan.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl with a fork. Mixture will be quite sticky, and it should be.
Spoon sticky mixture into frying pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: glazed baked ham
directions: Bake ham in a 325° oven, allowing 30 minutes per pound.
One hour before baking is complete, remove and score ham in diamond design.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, salt and nuts. Set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and vanilla; add to dry ingredients. Do not overmix. Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield: 24 brownies.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and chopped nuts; press into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Grill chicken with fajita spice sauce.
Saute onions, green pepper and red pepper in oil until soft.
Do not burn.
Warm tortilla shells according to package directions.
Slice lime in quarters.
Serve warmed tortillas with chicken, onions, pepper and garnishes of salsa, sour cream and guacamole.

title: betsy's pineapple squash
directions: Add last three ingredients to cooked squash and mound on squash.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: david's sprout pizza
directions: Spread dough on greased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Sprinkle sliced shallots on dough.
Arrange sliced avocado on dough, evenly distributed.
Cover dough to edges with a layer of sprouts (be generous, they bake down).
Sprinkle with dried oregano to taste. Cover with sliced Muenster cheese.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Salt and pepper. Cook on low heat overnight or all day.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix ingredients together, adding one egg at a time.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and
butter or margarine (melted); spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes. Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread carefully on pretzel mixture; mix strawberry Jell-O until dissolved with 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Refrigerate until almost jelled.
Put onto cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: crock of turkey tetrazzini
directions: Put into crock in the order listed.
Cover and cook on high 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown beef, garlic and onion in a heavy skillet.
Drain off excessive fat.
Gradually add remaining ingredients.
Place in crock-pot (3 1/2-quart size).
Never fill crock-pot too full; leave at least 1 inch from top.
Cook on high for 1 hour or simmer on low for 5 to 8 hours.

title: maple-mustard glazed chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the maple syrup, vinegar, water, mustard and salt. Bring to a boil; immediately reduce to a simmer and cook for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and whisk in the oil. Cool to room temperature. Cut the chicken into pieces weighing about 4 ounces each. Place in a shallow dish or sealable plastic bag and coat with enough sauce to cover. Let the chicken marinate for 30 minutes to 2 hours (in the refrigerator). Turn several times. Preheat and prepare the grill. Grill chicken for 4 minutes, then brush with the marinade; turn and continue to cook until done, about 5 to 8 minutes longer.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine the zucchini, eggs, onion, salt and cheese.
Gradually stir in flour and baking powder until well combined.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful into deep hot fat (365°) and fry for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: With a mixer, combine first 5 ingredients.
Cut each slice of bread into 4 square pieces.
Place a spoonful of mixture on half the bread pieces.
Top with remaining bread squares.
Top with another spoonful of cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Roll biscuit out in circle on floured board.
Sprinkle equal and cinnamon all over biscuit.
Put apple sauce on one side of biscuit-take the other half of biscuit and cover apple sauce. Press the edges together.
Fry in hot oil (A grown-up needs to do this part) until brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Take out and drain on paper towels.
Eat while warm with cold milk.

title: potato flour sponge cake
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar; continue beating. Add well beaten egg yolks and lemon juice.
Fold in the potato flour.
Place in baking pan; bake in slow oven (325°) for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter, beating until light and fluffy.
Add sugar; beat until smooth.
Stir in chopped pecans. Spread cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle top and sides with 1 cup coconut and gently press into frosting.
Garnish with pecan halves.

title: soft and chewy molasses cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and 1 cup sugar; blend in molasses and egg.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon,
ginger and cloves; add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Roll balls in remaining sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: lemon curd
directions: In heavy saucepan or double boiler, combine butter, sugar, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Cook over low - simmering heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens enough to heavily coat the back of a spoon.
Use wood spoon to stir mixture.
Don't let mixture boil or it will curdle.
Pour curd into small bowl or jar and stir in zest.
Use as is with toast, scones, tarts, cake fillings or mix with 1/2 cup whipped cream or 1/4 cup Cool Whip. Also good to add to parfait.

title: country chicken pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg.
Prepare pie crust.
Put in pan and spoon chicken mixture into crust and spread evenly.
Cut slits in top crust.
Place over chicken mixture.
Flute edges and brush with egg beaten with 1 tablespoon water.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown and inside is bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: artichoke relish
directions: Wash artichokes and trim as needed.
Soak overnight in brine of 1 cup salt to 1 gallon water.
Next morning, drain well.
Using coarse blade, grind artichokes, onions and pepper.
Mix in mustard seed, 1/4 teaspoon salt and turmeric.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar and bring to boil.
Combine mixtures.
Bring to rolling boil. Pack hot into 1/2 pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles; wipe jar rims.
Adjust lids and process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: *To make sour cream, add 2 tablespoons white vinegar to 1 pint canned milk.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, water, seasonings and bouillon granules in 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave at High 7 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring after half the cooking time.
Combine 1/4 cup milk with flour until smooth.
Stir flour mixture, remaining milk and butter into potato mixture. Microwave at High, uncovered, 7 to 10 minutes or until thickened, stirring several times during cooking.
Makes 1 quart.

title: cashew-rice milk
directions: Blend
until smooth with 1 to 1 1/2 cups water.
Gradually add 1 to 2 cups water and liquefy.
Add water to make 1/2 gallon. Strain and serve or refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.
May top with more Cool Whip if desired.

title: katie's christmas kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar and salt.
Add sugar, slowly.
Add food coloring for color, i.e. pink or green. Add chocolate chips.
Fold in. Drop on cookie sheet with foil on sheet.
Place in oven which has been preheated to 350°.
Turn heat off.
Let cookies set in oven. Leave in until cool.

title: chili pie casserole
directions: Place 2 cups of corn chips in a baking dish.
Arrange chopped onion and 1/2 cup grated cheese on the corn chips.
Pour chili over the onion and cheese.
Top with the remaining chips and cheese. Bake at 350° until hot.

title: nachos
directions: Place nacho chips on cookie sheet.
Spread refried beans on chips.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Ask your mom to place in oven on broil setting until cheese is melted.

title: lewis cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, salt,
peppers, onions and pineapple together. Make a ball and roll in pecans.

title: back to school cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses, beat well. Stir in vinegar, evaporated milk.
Mix and sift dry ingredients. Add molasses mixture.
Drop from tablespoon on greased sheets. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: stir crazy cake
directions: Pour flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, cocoa, soda and salt into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Stir with a fork.
Form 3 wells.
Pour oil in one, vinegar in one and vanilla in one.
Pour cold water over all and stir.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon; sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yap, yap, casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add soups.
Layer sauce, noodles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Crust:
Combine Bisquick, margarine and boiling water, stirring vigorously until very soft dough forms.
Press dough firmly into pie plate.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in 450° oven. Cool.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs; add creamed corn, whole corn with liquid, sour cream, oleo and corn muffin mix.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 greased pan until brown and done.

title: layered broccoli souffl
directions: Melt 1/4 c. butter in a saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt. Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Add milk, stirring constantly, and cook until thickened.
Stir in sour cream and remove from heat.
Place half of the broccoli in a buttered casserole dish. Arrange half of the cheese slices over the broccoli and then top with half of the white sauce.
Repeat.
Sprinkle cornflake crumbs evenly over final layer of white sauce.
Drizzle remaining melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
When chilled, roll into finely chopped nuts.
Decorate with 1/2 cherry on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: favorite chicken and potatoes
directions: In nonstick pan or pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, brown chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Add water, wine, onion and pepper.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Cover and simmer until chicken and potatoes are tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve, pouring extra broth over potatoes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans; mix well.
Shape into 4 inch ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Yields one cheese ball.

title: congealed pineapple salad
directions: Mash cream cheese. Heat to boiling the pineapple juice and Jell-O. Cool. Add cream cheese, pineapple, pecans and coffee cream. Garnish with cherries and pecans. Chill.

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Place above ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Heat oven to 325°. Great for 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Saute onion until golden.
Steam squash until tender, but still crisp.
Add squash, cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
Turn into casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs; dot with remaining butter. Bake 45 minutes or until set and lightly browned.

title: crock-pot meat balls
directions: Make into walnut-size balls. Do not brown. Put into greased crock-pot.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together flour, butter and sugar.
Press this into a 9-inch pan and bake 8 to 9 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, 10x sugar and Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust.
Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to a boil, then add 1/2 box small jello and boil until dissolved.
Spread over cream cheese mixture when it starts to jell.
Arrange fruit over the top from center out.
Can also use fresh peaches.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; let stand 5 minutes.
Be sure water is not hot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set until it rises (double in size).
Pour onto floured board; knead about 8 minutes.
This can be put in refrigerator and covered.
You may use small amounts at a time.

title: campbell's mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown hamburger meat with onion in a large skillet.
Drain and add peppers, taco sauce and tomato sauce.
Let simmer.
In saucepan, heat soups and milk over low heat.
Add to meat.
Cut tortillas in strips.
Place layers of tortillas, soups and meat mixture in a buttered shallow casserole dish.
Repeat until filled; end with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Cut partially frozen steak across grain, diagonally, into thin slices.
Cut slices in 1 1/2-inch strips.
Combine 3 tablespoons soy sauce, 2 tablespoons cornstarch, 2 tablespoons oil and gingerroot.
Stir in meat strips.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours.
Stir together broth, remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce, remaining 2 tablespoons cornstarch and oyster sauce; set aside.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water together and let cool.
After Jell-O cools, add orange sherbet to Jell-O.
Stir together then add fruit and chill.
If too sweet, add 1 cup chopped celery, 1 1/2 apples, chopped.

title: melt in your mouth pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Mix Hellmann's mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese together. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Stir again.
Starting with the lettuce, layer each ingredient in container.
Gently spread previous mixture on top of salad.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix milk with mushroom soup. Add all other ingredients except cheese. Mix well. Pour into a large greased casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 3 minutes. Serves 10.

title: billie doris warren's pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well and add oil, eggs, pineapple and vanilla.
Stir well until mixed.
Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and coconut. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: veg-all stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients; set aside.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil 1 large fryer chicken, have water deep enough to float the chicken.
Boil until meat falls off bones.
Bone the chicken. In large pot melt lard to 1/8 inch deep. Mix flour and chili powder, add this to chicken broth.
Warm flour tortillas and draw through sauce.
Place in a baking dish.

title: snickers pie(serves 6)
directions: In a double boiler or heavy boiler, melt the candy, peanut butter and half and half over medium-low heat.
Stir constantly until smooth.
Cool slightly.
Add Cool Whip (fold).
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Top with more Cool Whip and Hershey's syrup.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers and bananas in pan, beginning and ending with wafers.
Mix pudding mix according to package directions. Pour over banana and wafer layers.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix and let stand 10 minutes before pouring on the first 2 mixtures.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: della's chilli
directions: Cook and brown beef, onion, chili powder and salt.
Bring all to boil and thicken with cornstarch.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes or longer.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients (all but walnuts and parsley) by pressing in wax paper, then roll into a ball.
Roll in walnuts and/or chopped parsley.
Refrigerate.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Dice tomato, jalapeno and red onion.
Mix together with lime juice and cilantro.
Let set at room temperature for 4 hours. Serve!
Serves 4.

title: pineapple and cheese(dessert or side dish)
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Make a sauce of sugar, butter, flour and 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Spread pineapple in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Drizzle sauce over pineapple.
Spread Cheddar cheese over pineapple.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Crush Ritz crackers; add to pan.
Brown slightly; spoon over cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: baked green bean casserole
directions: Place cooked beans in baking dish.
Dilute soup with water or milk and pour over beans.
Season to taste.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix oleo, flour, sugar and eggs.
Add milk.
Blend mixtures together.
Add corn and mix well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until done.

title: grandma winnie's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and lard.
Add eggs to this.
Beat very well. Sift baking powder and flour together.
Put soda in milk. Alternate adding dry ingredients and liquid to creamed sugar and lard.
Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: frozen passion
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients.
Turn into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze to a firm mush, about 1 hour.
Break into pieces and turn into large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Return to pan and freeze until firm.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Toss lightly and spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good way to use leftover chicken or turkey.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place in layers in casserole dish, except onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes longer.
Uncover; sprinkle with French fried onion rings.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool; prick cake with fork and pour milk over cake.
Let set several hours or best if sets overnight.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle on coconut.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add one egg at a time.
Add flavoring and flour.
Beat for 15 minutes.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and bananas, beat well. Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts; pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool well, store overnight before cutting.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Set aside 1/4 cup flour.
Combine remaining flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with yogurt, beating well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Dredge pecans in reserved flour and fold into batter.

title: ice water chocolate cake
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch floured and greased pan.
This is a real moist cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine first 9 ingredients.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add 3 1/2 cups milk and the pimento.
Heat soup just until milk is hot.
Blend flour with 1/2 cup milk; stir into soup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add butter or margarine.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Add 1 1/4 cups of sugar and melted oleo to the beaten eggs; beat together.
Add milk, vanilla, and broken up bread.
Mix together.
Pour in baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coconut black walnut cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in nuts and coconut flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.
Pour hot coconut syrup over hot cake.
Allow to remain in pan 4 hours.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour in large bowl.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in water and margarine.
Mix in enough flour to make soft dough.
On floured surface, knead 4 minutes.
On greased sheet, roll dough to a 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread dressing down center third of dough length. Top with layers of beef, cheese and sauerkraut.
Cut 1-inch wide strips along sides of filling out to dough edges.
Alternating sides, fold strips at an angle across filling.
Cover dough; place over long, shallow pan 1/2 filled with boiling water for 15 minutes.
Brush with egg white; sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash 'bout 2 pounds spinach...dry wid papur towels...tear leaves apart 'n toss wid dressin'.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together than add milk slowly.
cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
When thickened add butter and vanilla.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: merry berry bars (cranberry)
directions: First layer:
Combine oatmeal, flour, sugar and margarine. Mix until crumbly, reserving 1 1/2 cup mixture.
Press in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange-glazed pecans
directions: Mix and cook all in iron skillet on medium heat until light golden, stirring constantly (about 10 minutes).
Pour onto waxed paper and break apart as soon as cool enough to handle.
Great for parties.

title: no cook peanut butter chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Quickly add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper.

title: pan-roasted corn with green onions
directions: In 12-inch skillet, melt butter. Add onion, garlic and chili powder; cook 7 minutes to brown lightly. Add corn, green onions, salt and pepper. Cook until corn is just tender. Add cilantro. Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Place sausages in a slow cooker.
In a bowl combine the pie filling, pineapple and brown sugar; pour over sausages.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hours.
Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush chocolate wafers and add butter; mix well.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with softened ice cream.
Top with cold fudge sauce.
Store the pie in the freezer for about 10 hours. Slice the pie into 8 portions and serve with whipped cream and diced almonds.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: Beat together very well sugar, butter, shortening, egg yolks and potatoes.
Add all at once, sifted dry ingredients, milk and nuts.
Stir until well blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Spread evenly into a lightly greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese cornbread
directions: Cream
butter,	salt
and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs;
beat
well.	Mix all dry ingredients and gradually add
to mixture,
alternating
with
water.
Scrape
side and bottom of bowl;
beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.	Pour in cheese	and beat 1 minute.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Serves 20.

title: zucchini skillet
directions: Stir and cook vegetables in butter over high until tender, about 15 minutes.
Top with cheese before serving.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a well-greased Bundt pan, sprinkle your pecans.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll into balls.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit balls in mixture until completely coated.
Drop all around the Bundt pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar all around the biscuit rolls.
Melt butter and pour over everything.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes in pan. Enjoy!

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, morsels and nuts. Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: chewy coconut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, cream butter.
Add sugars gradually, beating thoroughly.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Stir flour mixture into creamed mixture gradually mixing until blended.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes or until cookies just begin to brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Mix sugar and cocoa in small bowl.
Sprinkle cocoa mixture over top of mixture in pan.
Add hot water over top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, shortening and molasses.
Sift flour; measure and sift with baking soda, salt and spices.
Add alternately with water to first mixture.
Beat until well blended. Bake in greased pan at 375° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tops off bell peppers.
Scoop out seeds and membranes.
Discard.
Heat a large skillet.
Add beef and onion.
Cook about 5 minutes until beef is browned; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix to skillet.
Cook about 5 minutes more.
Add rice, mixing well.
Cook for 3 minutes longer.
Scoop beef mixture into peppers.
Place in a baking dish.
Add about 1/4-inch water to dish; cover.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer.

title: ladybird johnson's strawberry icebox pie(april, 1965)
directions: Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening. Sprinkle with water, tossing gently to moisten.
Roll out and fit into large, deep-dish pie plate.
Bake in hot oven until golden brown.
Cool.

title: cheddar scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook onion until tender. Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: deviled ham rolls
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Spread with butter.
Mix deviled ham and sweet pepper relish, then spread ham mixture over each roll. Then roll up rolls.
(You can also cut each triangle in half and make 16 smaller crescents.)
Roll starting at wide end.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: elegant fruit combo
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Place peach halves in a bowl; cover and set aside.
In a 1-quart casserole, stir together reserved peach syrup, cranberries and sugar.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix jello with water and rest of ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate and let jell.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° in a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool slightly and cut in squares.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all but rhubarb well.
Cut rhubarb in 1-inch lengths, fold into other mixture.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.

title: meatzza
directions: Spread pizza sauce over meat crust.
Arrange sliced vegetables on top.
Top with cheeses and oregano.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This is like a pizza, but the meat is the crust.

title: a favorite dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° until almost brown, about 20 minutes.
Cream the cheese; gradually add powdered sugar.
Fold in one cup Cool Whip. Spread on the cool crust.
Prepare pudding as directed on package; cool, stirring constantly.
Do not chill.
Carefully pour or spread over the cheese layer.
Spoon the pie filling over the pudding layer.
Spread the remaining Cool Whip over the cherry layer.
Top with coconut, if desired.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.
Makes about 18 servings.

title: mocha-walnut sauce
directions: In measuring cup, dissolve freeze dried coffee in boiling water; set aside.
In heavy gauge saucepan, combine heavy cream and sugar.
Bring just to boil, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Add chocolate morsels, butter and coffee; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks. Gradually stir in 2 tablespoons chocolate mixture; mix well. Return to chocolate mixture in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in walnuts.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs until well blended; add dry ingredients to mixture and add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Grease and flour an oblong pan; bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallows on top; return to oven for 10 minutes or until marshmallows have melted (watch closely).

title: almond swirl ring
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well. Arrange rolls
in
pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to
a
boil, stirring frequently.
Add 1 to 2 cups pecan pieces
(to

Drizzle

with

which has been sprayed with oil. Cover with a towel.
Let rise at room temperature overnight or 7 hours. Grease

13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 25 minutes.
Tip out upside-down on serving tray.

title: vanilla delight
directions: Butter a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch flat baking dish.
Crush vanilla wafers and cover bottom of dish with half of the wafers.
Cream together the butter, confectioners sugar, vanilla and eggs. Spread this mixture over the crumbs.
Whip the cream.
Drain the pineapple and add to whipped cream.
Spread cream mixture on top of butter mixture.
Top with remaining crushed wafers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: teriyaki bean special
directions: In a medium skillet, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender.
Add green beans, bean sprouts, chopped mushrooms and soy sauce; mix lightly.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with additional soy sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves.
In a small saucepan, combine water and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add sour cream and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into pans.
Bake 40 minutes.
Cool in pans on rack.
Frost.

title: eggplant elegant
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; cook until tender, stirring often. Remove from heat. Add butter, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Blend together; blend well and add crumbs to absorb all liquid. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan with butter, cover bottom with chopped pecans, saving about 1/3 cup for top.
Sprinkle with pudding mix.
Melt butter, add sugar and cinnamon and blend well.
Pour evenly over rolls (do not thaw).
Cover with cloth and set in warm place overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then turn out and serve.

title: orange cinnamon french toast
directions: In shallow bowl, combine egg product, orange juice and cinnamon. Preheat nonstick skillet sprayed with vegetable oil spray over medium heat. Dip bread in egg product mixture to coat both sides. Fry bread slices approximately 2 minutes on each side or until browned. Makes 2 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla. Mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix together and bake in rectangular pan like a regular cake.

title: lil' porkers
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook cabbage, onion and carrot until tender.
Stir in pork, water and mustard, then add shredded cheese.
Separate crescent dough and cut each triangle in half.
Press to flatten slightly.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of pork mixture into the center of triangle.
Pull corners to center over pork mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 32.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and pour into greased casserole.
Top with 1/2 pound sharp Cheddar cheese, grated.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: copper pennies(must do ahead)
directions: Boil carrots 3 minutes with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Drain and cool. Alternate layers of carrots, green peppers and onions.
Blend remaining ingredients and cook in saucepan until heated.
Pour over veggies.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours to marinate.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt morsels over medium heat, careful not to scorch.
Pour over noodles and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Sounds terrible.
Tastes great.

title: smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Add more milk if needed to get to milkshake consistency.

title: orange sauce
directions: Mix; boil 5 minutes.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Dip chicken in 1
cup
buttermilk,
then roll in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and put chicken
skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn
chicken
and bake 15 minutes more. Blend remaining 1 cup
of
buttermilk
and
soup.
Pour
over chicken. Bake 15 minutes more or until done.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic, celery, green pepper, in olive oil or butter.
Add all other ingredients except pasta and cheese.
Cook until all vegetables are tender.
Add cooked pasta.
Top each bowl with grated cheese.
Serves 12.

title: noel bowl(makes 10 servings)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar and let stand 1 hour.
Strain sugar syrup into large bowl.
Stir in apple cider, orange and lemon juices.
Cover and refrigerate.
(Can be prepared 2 days ahead.)
Serve warm or cold, depending on preference.

title: chili lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add lasagna, beans, meat, water, chili powder and salt; mix well. Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg, milk and oil together; pour over cornmeal mixture and mix well. Spoon dumplings onto heated chili lasagna mixture and cover. Simmer 20 minutes or until dumplings are set.
Serves six.

title: great grandma jones' tomato aspic
directions: Mix jello and heated tomato juice together.
Add rest.
Chill in greased mold.

title: watergate salad
directions: Empty pudding mix into bowl; stir in pineapple (juice and all).
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in a shallow dish.
Chill before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and sugar.
Add mixture of water, egg and vinegar.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or as a sandwich spread.
Add a bit more mayonnaise and serve as a dip with assorted crackers, chips and/or toasted bread pieces.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peach muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pans.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a 2-cup glass measuring cup, stir together the milk, butter and egg.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are completely moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fold in peaches.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until muffins are golden and center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan; serve warm.

title: shrimp and papaya with asian dunk sauce
directions: Peel and seed the papaya. Cut into 3/4-inch chunks.
Mix with the cilantro and mound on a platter.
Beside it, arrange the shrimp.
In a bowl, stir the lime juice and fish sauce or soy sauce, sugar and dried red hot chilies.
Spear fruit and shrimp with tiny forks to dip into sauce.
Serves 12.
Preparation time: 16 minutes. Cooking time: 0 minutes.

title: sliced baked spuds
directions: Slice potatoes into wedges; spread butter all over potatoes and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake on cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chick 'n ham fried rice
directions: (If you do not use monosodium glutamate, substitute 1/4 teaspoon of sugar.)

title: fettuccine with shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen, halve lengthwise and set aside.
Cook mushrooms, onion and garlic in oil in a large saucepan until onion is tender, but not brown.
Combine wine, bouillon granules, basil, oregano, cornstarch and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add to saucepan, cook and stir until bubbly.
Add shrimp to wine mixture.
Cover and simmer about 2 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Stir in tomatoes and heat thoroughly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Wash, peel and cook potatoes.
While cooking potatoes, brown and drain hamburger.
Mash potatoes with butter and milk.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate at least 2 hours.
Drain and serve with tortilla chips.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water together slowly for 10 minutes.
Cream together shortening, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add raisin mixture; mix together well.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: ham party casserole
directions: Make white sauce and add cheese and almonds.
Arrange potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with green beans.
Pour half of cheese sauce over beans and potatoes.
Add ham and remaining sauce.
Mix melted butter with crumbs.
Sprinkle over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix pork with beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Pat meat mixture out flat on tinfoil.
Spread stuffing over meat and roll up like a jelly roll.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *Use only 2/3 of these cans of soup.

title: cherry-o-cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature. Whip until fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk, continuing to beat well. Pour into crust. Chill 2 to 3 hours before garnishing top of pie with cherry pie filling.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Sift corn meal slowly in boiling water.
If lumpy, use egg beater.
Stir constantly.
Cook 15 minutes.
Brown hamburger, onions, pepper and mushrooms, then add tomatoes.
Season to taste. Cook 10 minutes.
Put one layer of corn meal in baking dish, then pour in meat sauce.
Put in 1/2 of olives.
Then put rest of corn meal on the top and put rest of olives on top.
Put in oven and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mock pink champagne
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Stir in juices; chill.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add potato chips, walnuts and flour.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Press flat with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 24 servings.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Coarsely grind cranberries and apples.
Add orange and rind (optional).
Add nuts.
Mix Jell-O, water and sugar until dissolved.
Add berry mixture.
Stir well and refrigerate overnight.
Take out and stir again.
Can double the batch to make more.

title: acapulco after dinner drink
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Keep in airtight container.
Use 1 heaping tablespoonful per 8 ounce cup of water.

title: crock-pot turkey breast
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water. Mix with cranberry sauce and pepper. Pour mixture over turkey breast in crock-pot. Cook on low all day.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, butter, extract, eggs and milk.
Add to flour mixture and stir.
Mix in pecans and lemon peel.
Bake for about 50 minutes at 350° in a greased loaf pan.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef with onions; drain.
Add tomatoes, sauce, paste and salt and simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes; stir occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles per package instructions.
Mix cottage cheese and eggs; add small amount Mozzarella cheese.
Assemble in layers alternating with meat, cheese, noodles, etc.
Bake in 350° oven 1/2 hour.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Line 13 x 9 pan with foil, so foil covers sides of pan.
In large pan combine butter, cream cheese and chocolate.
Heat just until melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar one cup at time.
Mix well after each addition. Press into pan and refrigerate to set.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; press on a cookie sheet.
Add peanuts and refrigerate.

title: famous yam balls
directions: Bake 6 sweet potatoes or canned potatoes.
Mash and mix sugar and pineapple.
Take large marshmallows and wrap potatoes around them.
Roll in coconut and place in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate before serving.

title: paella
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion, 1/2 of the parsley, tomatoes and garlic in the olive oil in a large frying pan or wok on medium heat for 1 minute. Add chicken thighs, ribs and sausage. Brown the meats.
Add uncooked rice, wine, peas and carrots, olives, capers, water, Zason' seasoning, Zason with saffron, salt and pepper to taste and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp, mussels, clams and rest of parsley. Cover the pot.
Lower the heat to simmer until rice is cooked and tender (approximately 3/4 hour).
That's it!

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Mix egg yolks and sugar very well.
Add coffee once cooled, then add chocolate.
Beat heavy cream to form whipping cream.
Fold into chocolate mixture and freeze until ready to use.

title: andy's favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix butter and peanut butter with wooden spoon. Add both kinds of sugar; stir until mixed.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until mixed.
In medium bowl, mix flour, soda and salt. Gradually add flour mixture to sugar mixture, mixing well.
Form dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: russian tea
directions: Use 1 tablespoon or more mix per cup and add hot water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into loaf pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown in 325° oven.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: marshmallow divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and salt; boil for 2 minutes (to make syrup). Put Marshmallow Creme in a bowl and pour syrup over it all at once. Add nuts.
Stir until mixture starts to lose its gloss.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan or drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Makes 3 layers or 2 layers and 6 cupcakes.
Sift flour and dry ingredients.
Add oil, coffee, milk and sugar.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Add 2 eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes. Batter will be thin.
Bake in 3 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) pans.
Line bottom of pan with wax paper.
Grease pans.
Grease wax paper.
Use 1 3/4 cups cake batter per pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Turn on cooling racks.

title: mushroom business
directions: Butter an 8-inch square baking pan or 1-quart casserole dish. Place 1/2 of the bread slices in the bottom.
Combine the mayonnaise with the salt and pepper, sauteed mushrooms and the finely chopped vegetables.
Spread over bread.
Cover with another layer of bread squares.
Combine the eggs and milk; pour over all. Cover and refrigerate overnight or all day.
One hour before serving, pour soup on top and spread around.
Add another layer of lightly buttered bread squares.
Sprinkle the cheese over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour or until puffed and brown.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; stir in lemon rind and add egg yolks. Beat until well blended.
Add flour alternately with lemon juice and milk.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour batter into buttered baking 9 x 9-inch dish or deep pan.
Set dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. When done, the cake is a delicate brown and the lemon sauce is on the bottom.
Very good!
Serves 8.

title: cherry sauce for ham
directions: Drain cherries.
Save juice.
Add enough water to reserved juice to make 1 cup.
Combine sugar and cornstarch and stir into cherry liquid to blend.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Stir in cherries and 1/4 teaspoon red food coloring and serve hot with ham.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
It will puff up and then fall.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Add cranberries, celery and orange.
(Also add grapes and nuts at this time, if desired.)
Mix well.
Pour in mold and chill until set.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Reserve 1 cup cake mix. Combine remaining cake mix with 1/2 cup melted butter and 1 egg. Press into greased pan.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and milk, stirring well.
Spoon sauce evenly over chicken; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Add 1/2 tablespoon of salt to 3 cups of cold water.
Wash mushrooms in this.
Drain.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine in mixer bowl and beat well the light cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Freeze. Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and Wesson oil.
Add soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt to flour.
Cut prunes in small pieces.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons of flour mixture to coat prunes and nuts.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to the creamed mixture.
After well mixed, fold in prunes and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan approximately 8 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips in top of double boiler. Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper until cooled.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla and beat well. Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir until well mixed.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Put confectioners sugar on top.

title: potato and corn flake casserole
directions: Cook, cool and dice potatoes.
Chop onion and peppers.
Add to potatoes.
Mix in oleo, cheese and bread cubes.
Stir in milk. Put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with corn flake crumbs.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken and chop well.
Mix together chicken, mushroom soup, sour cream and 1/2 can water in a casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: oyster bisque
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, celery salt and parsley.
Cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk gradually.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Stir in oysters and liquid.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve sprinkled with minced parsley.

title: three-pepper salad
directions: Seed peppers and cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Saute peppers in oil 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in seasonings.
Chill. Before serving, stir in jicama.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Pour
butter
into
applesauce	and stir good, then add soda. Stir
good.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together; add raisins and nuts last.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Casserole:
Mix Veg-All, onion, chestnuts and mayonnaise together and put in a greased baking dish.

title: grace's punch
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add ginger ale and soda last.
Add sugar to taste.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Makes fifty 4-ounce cups.

title: apple cider slaw
directions: Combine above with dressing, tossing to coat.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 2 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Makes 14-1/2 cup servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling evenly in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple chunks over cherries.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Cover with melted butter and top with coconut and nuts. Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, water and peanuts together in a heavy skillet.
Cook until golden brown and until the peanuts begin to pop, approximately 30 minutes.
Remove from fire and add the vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add soda and stir vigorously.
Pour onto a well-greased sheet pan.
Spread as thin as possible.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oatmeal, in saucepan.
Cook over medium to low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from fire and add oatmeal. Stir until oatmeal is coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Whip all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: white icing
directions: Mix and cook milk and flour until real thick; set aside to cool.
After first 2 ingredients are cooled, beat the remaining ingredients, then beat all together until smooth.

title: salty cake
directions: Beat the eggs; then add the oil, cheese, milk, baking powder and flour.
Pour mixture in a deep ovenproof pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and slice.
Can be served cold or hot.

title: deviled ground beef
directions: In large skillet, cook beef and onions, stirring with fork to break up meat, about 10 minutes or until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Sprinkle with flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Stir in water, Worcestershire and catsup.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 5 minutes or until sauce thickens and comes to boil.
Serve over mashed potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: california green salad
directions: Wash and drain lettuce and break into salad bowl.
Chop salami and add to salad.
Add the marinated artichoke hearts and onion rings, sliced from the Bermuda onion.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Toss with salad dressing just before serving.

title: quick and easy chicken cacciatore
directions: In a 10-inch square baking dish, arrange chicken, skin side down, with meatiest portions toward outside of dish.
Arrange green pepper and onion slices on top.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat until all is brown.
Add onion.
Cook until onion is clear and no longer firm.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and comino seed.
Stir to blend all flavors.
Add tomato sauce and stir as you add.
Add sugar and taste to adjust seasonings.
Add drained beans.
Stir gently.
Cover and cook on low for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cherry cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and add eggs.
Mix flour and lemon.
Mix well.
Smooth batter.
Outline 15 squares in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
On each square, put 1 tablespoon of pie filling on top.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cake is cool, sprinkle with more 10x sugar.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together milk and lemonade. Slowly stir in whipped topping, then lemon juice. Blend well. Pour into cooked pie shells and refrigerate.

title: minnie's cheesecake
directions: Butter spring-form pan and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla; mix well. Fold in sour cream.
Bake one hour in 350° oven.
Turn off oven and leave cake in oven 45 minutes to one hour with door closed.

title: party pizzas
directions: Fry ground beef and sausage; drain.
Add all other ingredients and cook until cheese is melted.
Spread on party rye slices. Place on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: crab cream cheese appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayo and lemon juice and spread in pie plate.
Spread flaked crab over and pour on cocktail sauce.

title: debi's mexican bean dip
directions: Be sure beans are dry; press out excess liquid with paper towel if necessary.
Lightly mash the beans so that there are still some whole ones left.
Add sour cream, salsa and half of the cheese. Mix. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue; put on pie.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbly, stirring occasionally.

title: brigham's sauce
directions: Scald 1 cup milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Boil for 2 minutes; cool slightly.
Add vanilla.

title: mexican hamburger casserole
directions: Brown about 1 1/2 pounds of hamburger.
Drain.
In a large bowl, mix together meat, beans and soup.
Crush up Doritos and place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish (1/2 package).
Spoon meat and bean mixture on top of chips.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies(club member: john waters)
directions: Cream oil, sugars and vanilla. Beat well. Stir in peanut butter; sift flour and stir into creamed mixture. Form into tiny balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with back of fork to make crisscross. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: banana pumpkin bread
directions: Puree bananas.
Combine with pumpkin, eggs and sugar in bowl. Beat in oil.
Add dry ingredients and just blend in flour until all flour is moist.
Add walnuts and blend in.
Do not overmix.

title: cornbread - special
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, including cinnamon.
Put oil and egg in the dry mixture.
Stir a drop.
Add 1 cup of milk. Stir well.
If too stiff, add a dollop more milk.
Mix in.
Put in 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Place in preheated oven at 350° and bake for 25 minutes.
It will pull away from the sides when done.

title: marinated coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage into large bowl.
Shred or thinly slice onion and pepper on top of cabbage.
Sprinkle sugar to cover entire top. Do not stir!
Then bring to a boil the salad oil, vinegar and dry seasonings.
Pour over other ingredients while hot.
Do not stir! Refrigerate at least 4 hours; overnight is better.
Keeps for several days.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well. Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill. Combine chocolate and cream in double boiler.
Cook, stirring constantly, over simmering water until chocolate is melted.
Stir in vanilla; keep warm.
Combine cream cheese and milk, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate mixture; mix well.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill; garnish with strawberries and powdered sugar.

title: scotch jumbles
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda and set aside.
Combine in a bowl the sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually blend flour mixture with milk; add creamy mixture.
Stir in rolled oats, Nestle butterscotch morsels, raisins and chopped nuts (if desired).
Drop by well rounded tablespoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Cook rice in water about 5 minutes and drain.
Add rice to onions, cheese and milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in 2-quart baking dish.
Stir once or twice during baking. Top with cheese about 20 minutes before done.

title: southern beef stew
directions: Place the meat in a slow cooker.
Toss with flour, salt and pepper.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir to mix well. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (or on high for 4 to 6 hours).
Stir before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, cream cheese, celery, onions, manicotti shells together.
(The shells can be cooked in the chicken broth.)
Put the Cheese Whiz on top (optional).
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: hot sweet mustard
directions: Mix the dry mustard with
1/3 cup water.
Let stand 25 minutes.
In another pan, mix together the cornstarch, salt, 1/3 cup water and sugar.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes; cool.
Add mustard mixture to pan; stir.
Yields 1 cup.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin strips.
In skillet, over medium-high heat, in hot oil cook beef and garlic until beef is browned.
Add onion.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover, simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles.
Yields 4 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.
Prep time:
10 minutes; cook time:
20 minutes.

title: oyster cracker nibbles
directions: Mix oil, salt, dill weed and dry mix together.
Pour over crackers, mix and stir.
Do not refrigerate.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Pour in large pot.
Add all ingredients and simmer slowly.
Serves 12.

title: easy chili with beans
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in olive oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring until ground beef crumbles; drain. Return mixture to Dutch oven; stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and chocolate kiss.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans; cook until thoroughly heated. Garnish if desired.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine ingredients in large skillet.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 35 or 40 minutes or until cabbage is done enough to suit your liking.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound in 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Top with mushrooms, onions and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover, cook 15 minutes more, basting occasionally.
Spoon sauce over meat.
Serves 8, 172 calories.

title: crunch cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, Crisco and eggs in mixing bowl until it is creamy and smooth. Beat about 8 to 10 minutes. Add vanilla and lemon flavoring. Mix well, about 1 minute. Pour into a slightly greased angel food cake pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. If cake is not brown, bake about 10 minutes longer, until it is firm and brown.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over cereal.
Stir until coated.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over and toss to coat.

title: oven "french fried" zucchini spears
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Spray a nonstick cookie sheet with cooking spray or wipe lightly with vegetable oil.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper on a sheet of wax paper. Quarter zucchini lengthwise and slice each spear in half to make shorter.
Place spears in plastic bag; add oil and water.
Close bag and shake until spears are lightly coated with oil.
Roll spears in crumb mixture until lightly coated.
Arrange spears in a single layer on pan.
Bake, uncovered, in oven for 7 minutes or until spears are browned and tender-crunchy.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel avocado and cut into chunks.
Mash with a fork, adding juice.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Place apples
in
unbaked shell.
Mix other ingredients and pour over apples;
add pecans to top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and 350° for 50 minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar, oil, eggs, Toasties and oats. Mix together flour; sift soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to flour and other mixture.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon or make into round balls and flatten with finger.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: grill apple tart
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Decore and slice apple. Slice with hole in middle of slice.
Place on grill to cook al dente.
Cut loaf in half.
Apply butter to bread.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar.
Place the bread on the grill to toast.
After apples are cooked and bread is toasted, place cheese on bread. Allow cheese to melt.
Place cooked apple on cheese.
Take Hershey bar.
Melt in microwave.
Swirl over apples.

title: easy sour cream coffee cake
directions: You will also need an angel or Bundt cake pan.

title: omelette
directions: Cook bacon or ham.
Beat eggs; pour in hot skillet with oil. Add cheese slices.
Crumble bacon.
Dice peppers and onions and add.
Cook until eggs bubble and hold together.
Then fold one side over other.
Cook until done.
Do not overcook or burn.

title: firehouse spaghetti
directions: Same as my Spaghetti, except substitute Ro-Tel tomatoes and the whole tomatoes for the 16-ounce whole tomatoes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Place ground beef, onion, salt and pepper in a skillet until done and slightly brown.
Drain grease.
Place ground beef mixture into a large pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 2 hours, stirring often.

title: baked apple
directions: Core apple.
Place in baking dish.
Fill center of apple with brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Pour water 1/4 inch into the baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until apple is tender.

title: orville's sister mabel's caramel corn
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, butter, cream of tartar and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until reaches 260° (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda quickly, but thoroughly.

title: egg crowns
directions: Remove yolks from eggs; put into a sieve over a bowl.
Place rings of white on buttered bread.
Sieve egg yolks and ends of whites.
Mix sieved eggs, cream cheese, mayonnaise, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Beat until smooth.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger and place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add more water if everything is not covered.
Turn heat to low and let cook for 6 to 8 hours.
You can serve "as is" for soup or add thickening to make stew.
Great recipe if you are going to be gone all day or need to leave a meal for loved ones.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream oleo with sugars,
add
eggs,
sift
flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add orange slices, nuts, oats	and
coconut.
Mix
all ingredients together and drop by
teaspoon
on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Fry bacon; add zucchini.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the eggs, margarine, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat for 15 minutes, no less.
Spread mixture on cooled crumb mix.
Put bananas on top of mixture.
Layer with pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans and cherries on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best if allowed to chill overnight.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Combine and put into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Spoon catsup over loaf.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add wet ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, pecans and oats last.
Bake on 350° for 8 minutes.
Great!!

title: sausage rigatoni bake
directions: Brown sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic until browned. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, oregano and pepper.
Add cooked pasta.
In a 3 qt. casserole dish put 1/2 noodle mixture, top with 1/2 cheese and rest of noodles.
Bake 350 for 35 minutes, top with rest of cheese bake 5 minutes longer.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.

Remove potatoes from water and put in bag and shake, coating potatoes well with mixture. Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once during baking. Done when golden brown.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs for 1 minute.
Add sugar and shortening and beat for 1 minute.
Add milk and vanilla, alternating with sifted flour and dry ingredients.
Turn out on floured surface (need to be floured well).
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out and decorate as desired. Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 8 minutes or until light brown.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Fry together ground beef, sausage, onions and peppers.
Drain. Add beans, tomatoes and seasoning mix.
Cook rice separately and mix with other ingredients.
Serve with salsa, if desired.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together pineapple, apple, celery, grapes, walnuts and kiwi.
In a small bowl, stir together the mayonnaise or salad dressing, yogurt and honey.
Fold gently into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: tomato vegetable soup(low calorie)
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water 20 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Cook carrots, celery and onion in 6 cups water until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and cooked macaroni.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 14 cups, 82 calories per cup.

title: marge's delight
directions: Mix together hamburger, onion, sugar, salt and pepper, and brown.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add soups, and noodles to hamburger mixture.
Layer hamburger mix in casserole pan with cheese in between layers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Place onion slices in unbaked pie shell.
Mix together the milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over onion rings. Top with about 3/4 inch of grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mom's brown rice
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in a skillet.
Pour in a baking dish and stir in soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cut in shortening; add buttermilk all at once.
Mix just until moistened, the batter will be very wet. Let sit about a minute or two.
Put about a cup of flour (same kind) in another pie pan.
Spoon biscuit dough into plate of flour. (I use ice cream dipper sprayed with Pam.)
Flour hands; shape biscuits, shaking off most of flour.
Put into round 8-inch cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Crowd together.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
When done, brush on melted butter.
Let cool on a wire rack or eat immediately!

title: texas pralines
directions: Line with foil a sheet cake pan.
Place whole graham crackers on foil, close together.
Bring other ingredients to a boil (it will be thick, but keep stirring).
After mixture boils, remove from heat and pour mixture over graham crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Score while warm.

title: holiday tossed salad
directions: Toss all ingredients. Just before serving, drizzle with raspberry vinaigrette.

title: rich herb dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl.
Covered, sauce will keep several days in the refrigerator.
Makes about 2/3 cup.
For maintenance diet, allow 3 tablespoons.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, adding 2 teaspoons red pepper while cooking.
Drain.
In a bowl, mix eggs, cream of corn, milk, corn meal, red pepper and salt.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased skillet.
Place a layer of ground beef, then add 1 chopped medium onion.
Next, layer cheese and add remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat peaches.
Melt butter and pour into casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together. Pour into dish over butter.
Spoon peaches into batter.
Pour juice in. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 25-30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with a small amount of milk to soften; spread over bottom of crust.
Put half of the berries on top of cheese covered crust.
Mash rest of berries and bring to boiling point. Mix sugar and cornstarch together; add to mashed berries.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cornstarch is smooth.
Cool and pour over fresh berries in pie shell.
Place in refrigerator until very cold.
Cover with slightly sweetened whipped cream before serving.
Save a few big berries for the top of each slice of pie.
Local berries are essential for this pie.
California ones just won't work.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup, cream cheese, milk, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Stir often until cream cheese is melted.
Pour in baking dish and bake for 20-25 minutes at 350 degrees.
If using biscuits on top, bake until brown.

title: vegetable crouton pie
directions: Microwave vegetables in casserole dish 9 minutes on High. Season with margarine, salt, pepper, garlic and Italian seasoning; set aside.
Mix together croutons and margarine.
Press into a 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Construct pie.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup of cheese on crust.
Add vegetables.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Beat eggs and add milk; stir.
Pour over the pie. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
A real crowd pleaser!

title: low-fat raisin-cinnamon bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water, not hot.
Set aside.
Heat milk, sugar, salt and margarine to lukewarm and then add this to the yeast mixture.
Stir in small amounts of both flours and the raisins and mix to form a stiff dough.
Turn onto a floured surface, knead 10 minutes, adding extra flour as needed. Shape into ball.
Place in bowl sprayed with nonstick spray.
Turn dough over to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap loosely.
Let rise in a warm place for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry frozen pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Reserve 1/2 cup berries and syrup for garnish.
Add remaining berries and syrup to cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Freeze firm.
Remove from freezer 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with strawberries and syrup.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, corn syrup and water in pan. Cook and stir until thickened.
Add gelatin and blend.
Cool. Put berries in cooled shell.
Spoon gelatin over berries.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sugar and spice coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, pecans, cinnamon and cereal.
Set aside.
Prepare cake mix using water required on package; add sour cream and eggs. Place 1/2 batter in bottom of pan; cover batter with 1 1/2 cups cereal mixture.
To the remaining cereal mixture, add 2 tablespoons butter.
