Crumble over batter.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: almond bars
directions: Mix together; spread and pat into a 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cook sweet potatoes with skins on until soft peel and mash. Add sugar, salt, melted butter and rich milk.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Pour in a buttered baking dish and top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Add eggs; beat until combined.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until set.

title: taco dip appetizer
directions: Mix beans and pepper juice (add some chopped pepper if desired) together in a bowl.
Mix 2/3 of taco seasoning in it, too.
Spread mixture in a dish or tray bottom (round plate like pizza looks great).
Mix 1/3 of taco seasoning with sour cream and spread over bean mixture.
Sprinkle the cheese and onion and tomato on top as desired.
Olives or mushrooms can be added if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add ingredients (except 1 cup pecans). Chill.
Roll in remaining pecans.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain off excess fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread
cup
meat
sauce.
Layer, a layer of lasagne noodles,
1 cup sauce and cheese that has been shredded, 1/3 of Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Repeat until all has been used.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together in large mixing bowl.
Put oleo, Crisco, water and cocoa in saucepan.
Put on stove and bring to high boil.
Stir into flour and sugar mixture.
Put eggs, soda, cinnamon, buttermilk and vanilla into a bowl.
Mix, then add to mixture.
Bake in shallow pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: congealed fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water; stir in hot water.
Add sugar and salt; stir until dissolved.
Blend in orange and lemon juices. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in grapes, fruit and nuts.
Put into a 5-cup bowl or mold.
Oil bowl or mold before putting in mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: easy barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring to crumble; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and onion; stir well.
Set aside.
Separate biscuits and place 1 each in muffin cups or muffin pan, pressing up sides.
Spoon meat mixture evenly into biscuit cups.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: chicken breasts with artichokes and peas
directions: Coat chicken strips with flour, salt and pepper mixture.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, add oil and cook chicken until lightly browned.
Add broth, wine, artichoke hearts and ham; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in peas.
Cook for 5 minutes more or until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with rice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13 dish with 1 can crescent rolls. Brown sausage (1 pound mild and 1 pound hot). Drain well. Mix sausage, cheese and eggs together. Spread on top of rolls. Put second can of crescent rolls on top of mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Bake in prepared pans for 65 to 75 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: wonder muffins
directions: Mash bananas and combine with all other ingredients.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin tin and fill 12 slots.
Bake for 22 minutes; remove muffins from tin and cool thoroughly before storing.

title: cream puff shells
directions: Heat to boiling the
water, butter and salt.
Add flour and then eggs, one at a time, until mixture is thick and shiny.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture on greased sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400°
for 25 minutes.
When cool, slit a small opening in the side.
Fill with pudding or whipped cream.

title: apple salad mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine juice and water. Add to jello and stir.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Add apple and celery, mix well.
Refrigerate until set.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour fruit over batter. Mix flour, sugar and vanilla. Pour in small amount of milk until smooth. Pour mixture over fruit. Bake 30 minutes or until brown in 400° oven.

title: banana pudding trifle
directions: Mix milk and pudding until it begins to thicken.
Let set in refrigerator for a few minutes; then add condensed milk, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Pour chocolate syrup randomly over layers; then sprinkle nuts over it.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: herb butter basted turkey breast
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil. Set aside.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar and eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 375° in angel food cake pan. Quick bread.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In 6-quart saucepot, cook spaghetti as label directs; drain.
Return spaghetti to saucepot; keep warm.
Meanwhile, in 2-quart saucepot or pan over medium heat in 3 tablespoons hot butter or margarine, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour until blended.
Gradually stir in milk, mushrooms with liquid, bouillon, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened. Remove pan from heat; stir in cheese.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla, oats and salt.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper to set.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together to make crumbs the flour, sugar and butter.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs and put aside for topping.
Put 1 teaspoon baking soda into milk; hold over mixture.
Stir to make foamy and then pour into crumb mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix together.
Pour mixture into well-greased pie pans.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: my favorite congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple tidbits together and bring to boil. Set aside to cool.
When cool, mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and chopped nuts together.
Stir into jello mixture.
Put into container.
Chill overnight.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to above mixture.
Stir in milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with raisins, brown sugar and milk if you want.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a large heavy saucepan. Heat to boiling. Stir constantly about 5 minutes over medium heat or until mixture reaches soft-ball stage; remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients; stir vigorously until well blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in a 4-quart bowl or casserole on High for one minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well. Microwave on High 5 minutes or until mixture begins to boil.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in chocolate pieces until melted. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: cool whip graveyard treat
directions: Mix 2 cups of the cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly onto bottom of pan. Refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese and remaining 1/4 cup sugar in bowl until smooth.
Stir in half of the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Stir boiling water into jello in bowl for 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into jello until slightly thickened.
Remove any ice. Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm.
Spread remaining whipped topping over jello.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
Decorate with assorted rectangle-shaped sandwich cookies to resemble a graveyard.
You can also decorate cookies with icing and add candy corn and pumpkins.

title: miniature cheesecake
directions: Line cupcake pans with liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In small bowl beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill liners 3/4 full with mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Top with filling.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Cook and drain sausage, place back in skillet.
Add cream cheese to sausage over medium heat.
Add Rotel tomatoes and cook until all are blended.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon jelly
directions: Combine lemons and water in a large stockpot over medium-high heat.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Strain fruit mixture, reserving liquid.
If necessary, add additional water to reserved liquid and sugar in stockpot over medium heat; stir until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat to medium-high and bring to a rolling boil.
Add pectin.
Stir until dissolved.
Bring to rolling boil again and boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam.
Tint to desired color.
Pour into jars and seal; then put into a hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix all together and put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Spoon off any grease which collects on top.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; combine juice, sugar, flour, eggs and butter.
Cook over medium heat slowly until thickened, stirring frequently.
Cool thickened sauce; add drained pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
It is also good with sliced strawberries.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet until browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain.
Add next 8 ingredients; pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover, stir and bake an additional 30 minutes, uncovered.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
If desired, garnish with mushrooms and bell pepper strips.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: no crust pie
directions: Melt margarine in pie pan.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cut apples in half and core.
Make pie dough and roll out in portions sized to wrap around each half of an apple.
Place 1/2 apple in center with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
Wrap dough around each apple half and place in large pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon cinnamon, 2 cups water and 1/2 stick oleo and bring to boil.
Let cool for a few minutes and then pour over apples.
Bake at 350° until crust browns.

title: tandy cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add to flour and baking powder mixture.
Blend well.
Bake in an 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread peanut butter across top.
Refrigerate until completely cool.
Top with 12 ounces of melted Hershey bars.
Refrigerate again until chocolate is set. (Melt chocolate bars in microwave on low setting.)

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Combine Jell-O with boiling water in large mixing bowl.
Stir until Jell-O dissolves.
Fold in strawberries with juice which have been thawed.
Then add drained pineapple, mashed bananas and nuts.
Turn 1/2 of mixture in 12 x 8-inch baking dish and refrigerate until firm.
Then spread sour cream on top.
Spoon on rest of strawberry mixture and refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl and toss.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake in 375° oven in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: butternut squash bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat shortening, eggs, water and squash. Combine with dry ingredients until dry mix is moist. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add thawed and drained spinach, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses and salt.
Cook and drain noodles.
Spread spoonful of meat mixture on each noodle; roll up.
Arrange, seam side down, in shallow casserole.
Prepare spaghetti sauce; spoon over rolls.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add to rice along with soups, Cheez Whiz and broccoli.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter waffles
directions: Cream together the peanut butter and shortening.
Add the sugar; beat and add the 2 eggs.
Stir in the milk.
The mixture will be very thin, of course, but stir well and the milk will blend in.
Sift together and add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until very smooth.
Bake in waffle iron.
This batter will also make dandy pancakes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir all together.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan in 350° oven until brown.

title: solano sunrise
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve over ice.

title: lo-cal salad dressing
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Dissolve the jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Drain the blueberries and pineapple and save the juice.
Add fruit and 1 cup juice to mixture and gel.
Blend sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Layer on top of congealed jello.
Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese's at room temperature.
Add rest of ingredients (except pecans).
Mix well and form into a ball.
Roll in pecans, cover and chill.

title: kentucky style fried chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll chicken pieces in mixture and cook for 1 hour. Top with liquid margarine.

title: punch cubes
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Place in a blender for a few seconds.
Pour into ice cube trays and freeze. Place 3 or 4 in a glass and pour chilled ginger ale over cubes for a refreshing drink for picnics and holidays.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally across grain in very thin strips.
Brown steak strips, 1/2 pound at a time, in hot oil.
Remove meat from skillet and set aside.

title: cheese soup
directions: Use only Velveeta and cube.
Combine first 9 ingredients. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, stirring until well blended.
Add milk mixture to vegetables.
Cook until thickened.
Add cubed Velveeta cheese; stir until melted.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all together.
Make balls size of walnuts.
Place in oil in hot pan.
Brown well on all sides.
Continue to cook until done.
Add can of cream of mushroom soup.
Using spatula, mix the soup well with meat balls until dissolved.

title: bobbi's summer salad
directions: Cut lettuce up fine.
Combine all ingredients into an extra large mixing bowl.
Toss well and often.
Serve immediately.
No dressing required.

title: lemon bars
directions: Work softened oleo into flour and powdered sugar.
Press with fingers into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hearty dip
directions: Combine all ingredients well and serve with chips, crackers or veggies.

title: broccoli marinade
directions: Steam the broccoli for 5 minutes. Place in container with cover.
Pour dressing and sugar over broccoli.
Stir lightly and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.

title: mom's chili
directions: Brown meat, then drain grease, but reserve.
Put finely chopped onion and bell pepper in reserved grease.
Fry until tender; drain.
Mix all other ingredients in stewing pot or Dutch kettle.
Cook on high for 30 minutes; reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad with bourbon
directions: Cut all melons into melon balls.
Peel pineapple; core fruit. Cut into cubes.
Wash, halve and seed grapes.
Combine bourbon, honey and walnuts.
Pour mixture over fruit one hour before serving to allow flavors to mix.
Add to appearance by serving in melon basket created from a watermelon half.

title: potato romanoff
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes until tender, about 20 to 25 minutes. Cool, peel and grate into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Mix well.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours, covered, or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: party mix
directions: Mix
together
all
of	the
ingredients and bake for 2 hours at 250° while stirring every 15 minutes.

title: granola cereal
directions: Use a large pan 2 to 3-inches high.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, mix well the honey, oil and vanilla. Pour over dry mixture.
Work with hands or large spoon.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toasty brown.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Add raisins after cereal is baked or they will be hard.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and cinnamon. Add Wesson oil and eggs; mix for 3 minutes. Mix in 3 cups of finely grated carrots and 1 cup chopped nuts. Stir with spoon. Bake at 300°.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine corn, cucumbers, onion and tomatoes in bowl.
Blend in sour cream with mayonnaise and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: prize winning buttermilk-coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter.
Mix well to dissolve sugar.
Melt butter and pour into egg mixture while hot.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 400 degrees until crust is lightly brown.
Reduce heat to 300 degrees and bake until set.
Total baking time is about 1 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Add lemon juice as needed to make mixture easily spreadable.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: one-dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: peanut butter cookie bars
directions: In mixer bowl, beat butter and peanut butter for 30 seconds. Add sugars, beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to the mixture and beat until blended.
Stir in the oats.
Spread into a greased 9x13 inch baking dish.

title: southern sangria
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients
in
a large pitcher, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add
grape	juice and gently stir to mix well.
Serve over crushed ice.
Yields 5 cups.

title: jenny's spice cake
directions: Can use pecans and candied cherries.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Set aside to cool.
Add yeast to 1/4 cup warm water.
To the cooled mixture add yeast and 3 cups flour; set aside to rise for 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until just tender; drain. Mash slightly; drain again.
Combine with sour cream, 1/4 cup margarine, onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Mix together bread crumbs and cheese.
Toss with 3 tablespoons melted margarine and sprinkle over squash. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
You can add 3/4 cup shredded sharp cheese to top of casserole.

title: beef stew(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper and dredge beef cubes in this well.
Heat oil in large Dutch oven or roaster casserole dish that can go on stove top and then into oven.
Brown beef on all sides, adding oil, if needed.
Pour tomato sauce over meat; scrape bottom of of casserole.
Add water.
Add carrots; mix well.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Add to the eggs, salt, pepper, cracker crumbs, pimento, cheese and milk.
Stir in the asparagus (cut up) and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until the custard is set, about 30 minutes.

title: now you see 'em now you don't cookies
directions: *Blended Oatmeal:
Measure oatmeal, then blend in a blender to a fine powder.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order in 3-quart dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil.
Add flour and stir. Mixture leans to sides of pot.
Put in mixer and add eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Spread into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove and chop stems.
In 1-quart casserole, combine stems, onions and butter.
Microwave at High 2 minutes or until tender.
Stir in bread crumbs, cheese and seasoning.
Pile in caps.
Arrange caps on paper towel lined plate with large caps to outside.
Microwave at High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until heated through.
Rotate plate once or twice during cooking.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix and pour into 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: florida key lime pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add sweetened condensed milk gradually until well blended.
Beat in yogurt, lime peel and food coloring until smooth.
In a separate bowl, whip the cream with sugar until small peaks form.
Gently fold 3/4 of the whipped cream into the cream cheese mixture.
Line the baked, cooled pie crust with 2 tablespoons almonds.
Spoon filling on top.
Chill at least 3 hours; garnish with remaining whipped cream, lime slices and 1 tablespoon toasted almonds if desired.

title: stuffed fish
directions: Make stuffing mix as it is on box.
Set aside to cool, then sprinkle fish real good with lemon juice, then stuff fish and roll up.
Place in a pan end on bottom.
Dot with butter and lemon juice.
Sprinkle parsley over fish and bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix only until moist.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let sit 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chocolate lover's cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with mixer until well blended. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips. Pour into crust. Bake 10 minutes. Without opening oven door, reduce temperature to 250°. Continue baking 30 minutes or just until set. Remove from oven to wire rack. Cool completely. Cover. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled. Place 1/2 cup chocolate chips and whipping cream in small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred. Cool slightly; spread over top of cheese pie. Refrigerate until topping is set.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, but the butter, together.
Put into a baking dish.
Slice the butter into small slices and place on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli, bacon, etc. just before serving.

title: broccoli bisque(soup)
directions: In medium saucepan, cook broccoli and onion in water until tender, 6 to 7 minutes.
In small bowl, whisk together salad dressing and flour.
Add to broccoli.
Cook over low heat until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese if desired.
Serve hot. Serves 3 to 4.

title: spice muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg. Beat egg and add sugar.
Stir well.
Add buttermilk and shortening. Add to flour mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full.
Brush tops of muffins with milk and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lazy crazy chocolate cake
directions: Add ingredients in order given; beat when all is added.
Add vanilla last, plus 1 cup boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Cut up and brown bacon, green pepper and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add peas, tomatoes and spices to taste.
Simmer and serve.

title: celery with corn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan or large skillet.
Add celery, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add corn and tomatoes, season to taste. Makes 6 servings.

title: beef paprika
directions: Add meat, onion and garlic to skillet sprayed with Pam. Cook and
stir
until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in catsup,
Worcestershire
sauce,
sugar,
paprika, mustard, cayenne and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover; simmer about 20 minutes. Blend flour and
cup
water;
stir
gradually
into meat mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over rice (or noodles).

title: buttermilk sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Combine next 3 ingredients and add to the mixture.
Divide dough and roll to about 1/4 to 3/8-inch thickness.
Cut and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone the chicken.
Mix with cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Layer crackers, like banana pudding, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crush one pack of crackers and put on top.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: canning apples for pie
directions: Cook all ingredients together in large kettle until thickened; add 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Fill quart jars 1/3 full with sauce; fill rest of jar with sliced apples.
Process for 20 minutes in hot water.
When cool to touch, turn upside down to make sure all sauce covers apples.
Store in cool dark place. When baking pie, just fill shell with apple mixture and bake. Great for winter treat.

title: bett's cabbage rolls from germany
directions: Wilt cabbage and set aside.
Fry bacon with chopped onion until brown and set aside.
In blender, add carrots, pepper and celery sticks. Add mushroom soup after vegetables are chopped. Add chopped bacon and onion to hamburger.
Add mushroom soup and vegetable mixture. Add bread crumbs or rice.
Make cabbage rolls and layer in roaster pan.
Mix V-8 juice and tomato paste.
Pour over rolls. Cook, covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 35 to 45 rolls.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In plastic bag or large bowl, shake or toss all ingredients until vegetables are coated.
Empty into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Discard bag.
Bake 20 minutes, stirring once, or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandma orr's fruit salad
directions: Drain together pineapple,
Mandarin oranges and cherries and keep the juice.
Mix together the egg yolk, flour and sugar with a fork.
Add enough drained fruit juice to this to equal 1/2 cup. Stir.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and marshmallows to taste.
To this, fold in one-half pint fresh whipping cream (whipped until it forms stiff peaks with 1 tablespoon granulated sugar).
Chill.

title: winter salad
directions: Drain the canned vegetables. Combine with the fresh vegetables. Marinate overnight in sauce of the remaining ingredients. After the vegetables have marinated for at least 10 hours, drain well and serve.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix dry pudding, butter, egg and flour.
Place in bottom of small baking dish.
Pour peaches onto this mixture.
Blend cream cheese with sugar and then add peach juice to make mixture thin. Pour this mixture over the peaches.
Bake on 350° until lightly browned on top.
This recipe can be doubled and will make an oblong baking dish full.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Make balls; press down with fork, then brush cookies with eggs.
Bake at 325° until golden brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carol's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo syrup until it spins a thread when poured from a spoon.
Add peanuts; cook until light brown.
Remove from heat; add soda and stir thoroughly.
Pour immediately into a greased cookie sheet.
After it cools completely, break up with a spoon.

title: better than baked beans
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, in large skillet over medium heat, fry bacon and onion until tender.
Stir in brown sugar, vinegar, garlic salt, mustard and salt.
Reduce heat to low and simmer.
Cover for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°. In a 3-quart bean pot or casserole dish, combine all beans.
Spoon onion-bacon mixture evenly over top.
Bake for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.

title: meatballs with noodles
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/2 cup milk, bread crumbs, onion, parsley and salt. Shape into 12 balls.
Heat oil in a large, heavy skillet.
Add meatballs and brown on all sides. Remove meatballs from skillet and set aside. Drain drippings and wipe skillet clean. Combine chicken soup and 1/2 cup milk in skillet. Add meatballs.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Cook noodles in a Dutch oven according to package directions. Drain and return to Dutch oven. Add meatball mixture, tossing well.

title: zucchini-oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, measure first 7 ingredients.
In a medium bowl, beat the eggs slightly and stir in zucchini and oil.
Stir this into the larger bowl with the first 7 ingredients, until flour is moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.

title: hidden treasure strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in fruit and nuts. Pour 1/2 of mix into 9 x 13 pan. Chill until firm. Store remaining mixture at room temperature. Prepare cheesecake filling according to package directions. Reserve crumbs for later use. Spoon cheesecake filling over congealed fruit mix. Spoon remaining gelatin mixture over filling and chill until firm. Yields about 18 servings.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover; chill.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool. Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice, milk and seasonings. Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: sunday morning coffee cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add shortening; cut in and save 3/4 cup of this mixture.

title: holiday-crown cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and milk.
Blend well.
Reserve 1/2 cup onions.
Stir in remaining onions and olives.
Shape into a ball; roll in reserved onions.
Garnish with stuffed green olive slices or as desired.
Serve with crackers or tiny party rye.

title: oatmeal cookies(lunchroom kind)
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanut butter and vanilla in boiler.
Bring to rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Spoon on waxed paper.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
To make tea, mix 2 tablespoons with 6 ounces of hot water.

title: crescent cookies
directions: In one bowl, sift flour and salt; set aside.
In another bowl, put 2 sticks butter; mix until fluffy.
Add sugar; mix well.
Mix in vanilla.
Mix in water.
Mix in flour (a little at a time). Add nuts (2 cups).
Make into balls; put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with 2 fingers.
Bake at 325°, depending on size of cookies.
Bake until light golden brown on top.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: impossible taco pie(6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch).
Cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix (dry).
Spread in pie plate, sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix 15 seconds in blender, 1 minute with beaters, until smooth.
Pour on meat.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomato and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Make brine of the vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to a boil. Place a generous layer of dill, 1/2 to 1 clove garlic (sliced) and 1/2 tablespoon mustard seed in bottom of each jar.
Pack cukes; when half full, add more dill and finish packing.
Fill jars within 1/2-inch of top with hot boiling brine.
Put caps and bands on.
Process in hot water bath 5 minutes.
These are very easy to make; will never fail or become soft.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, shortening, sugar, and salt.
Cool to lukewarm, add yeast softened in lukewarm water.
Add beaten egg. Gradually stir in flour to form a soft dough.
Beat vigorously. Cover and let rise in warm place till doubled in bulk
or about 2 hours.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Cut out in desired size, dip in 1/2 butter and 1/2 shortening which has been melted and cooled some.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours in roll pans.
Bake at 400 degrees to 425 degrees until brown.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt. Gradually blend into creamed mixture and add chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: eggs for breakfast
directions: Place bread crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or glass baking dish.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over bread crumbs.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until firm.

title: soup beans
directions: Put beans in large pan, cover with water 2 to 4 inches above beans.
Add several ham chunks, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender on medium high for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with cornbread and fried potatoes.

title: chew cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pour into a greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips and pecans.
Melt cream cheese and mix together with spoon the confectioners sugar and eggs.
Pour over top and bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together ahead of time.
Make frozen rings of this mixture to float in punch so it does not dilute drink. Chill fruit punch well.
Just before serving, add 2 large bottles ginger ale.
Serves 100.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel and boil in salted water eggplant until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut up and drain well.
Add eggs, 3 slices of dry bread crumbs, milk and 1/4 stick butter or margarine.
Add salt and pepper to taste and 4 ounces grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Top with another 4 ounces grated cheese and 4 slices day old bread crumbs rolled in 1/4 stick butter or margarine (melted).
Bake about 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: company swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 3 tablespoons of the melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly combine the pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and evaporated milk.
Pour into unbaked pastry shells.
Filling is generous.
Bake in hot oven, 400°, for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and outside comes out clean.

title: meat loaf in the crock-pot
directions: You will need 3 (18 x 2-inch) foil strips.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 4-quart casserole dish.
Saute meat with garlic until meat is pink.
Add all ingredients, except cheese.
Cut tortillas into strips and stir into mixture.
Put in oven.
When ingredients get bubbly, sprinkle on cheese.
Bake for about 15 to 20 minutes, until done.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Add 1 chopped tomato, salt, pepper, lemon juice, garlic powder, minced onion and hot pepper sauce; set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning; set aside.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except apples and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl at once.
Mix on medium speed about 18 to 20 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.
Do not preheat oven.

title: company apple pancake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Have ready a 9 to 10-inch (across bottom) ovenproof skillet, a 9-inch pie pan or an 11 x 7-inch baking dish. In food processor or blender, process eggs, milk, flour, salt and nutmeg until smooth.
Heat oil in skillet or pan.
When very hot, pour in batter.
Bake uncovered 18 to 20 minutes without opening oven door.
Pancake should be puffed, crisp around edges and golden brown.
Serve with sauteed apples and raisins

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring, until it crumbles.
Drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.
Set sausage aside. Add butter to drippings; heat over low heat until butter melts. Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in seasonings and sausage.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring.
Makes 3 3/4 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add frozen strawberries, stirring occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm (leave remaining mixture out).
Spread chilled and set mixture with sour cream. Pour remaining mixture on top; chill until firm.

title: sweet 'n sour baked beans
directions: Place onion rings in skillet bacon was fried in.
Add sugar, seasonings and vinegar.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add this to the beans.
Add bacon bits and place in 3 quart baking dish and bake until browned.

title: biscuits
directions: Prepare pancake batter.
Take a slice of bread and cut in half.
Dip into pancake batter.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Dot with butter and syrup.
Serve hot.

title: slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, pepper and carrots; set aside.
Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over cabbage mixture and salt to taste.
If you make a lot, just add more sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place chicken in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Add rice, vegetables and 1/2 can of French fried onions around top and under chicken.
Combine bouillon and Italian seasoning; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Top with remaining onions and bake 2 to 4 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, alternately with buttermilk and soda.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bake at 350° in three 8-inch pans or 1 sheet layer pan until brown and springs back.
Frost or serve plain.

title: orange raisin rice
directions: Melt margarine and add juice, water, salt, sugar, raisins and orange rind.
Bring to boil.
Add rice slowly and cover.
Reduce heat and cook 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat dry cake mix, water and eggs in large bowl on low 30 seconds.
Beat on high 2 minutes.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 11 minutes or until no indentation remains when touched. Cool 1 minute and remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack. Frost and decorate.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add pecans and mix well.
Combine other ingredients in bowl.
Add nuts and stir, coating well.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 45 minutes.
Stir often.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
After pudding has thickened, mix in with a box of chocolate cake mix.
Stir well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ham linguine florentine
directions: In heavy large skillet brown almonds 5 minutes.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
In same pan cook mushrooms and onions in butter until onions are tender, not brown. Stir in flour and thyme.
Add beef broth and milk or cream all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Cook 1 minute more. Stir in ham, parsley and half of almonds and mustard.
Stir in hot cooked linguine.
Place chopped spinach on a platter or individual plates and top with hot linguine mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup almonds on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesecake dreams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix brown sugar, flour and walnuts in small bowl.
Stir in margarine until well combined.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Pat mixture gently into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in another bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer until smooth. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle on remaining crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes until set.
Cool on wire rack, then cut into 2-inch squares and cut each square diagonally in half.
Makes 32 cookies.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in 2 quarts water until tender.
Cook peas 15 minutes.
Boil eggs.
Mix all together.
Put salt and pepper as you like.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Beat
together	milk, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add water, margarine
and
yeast
to egg mixture. Add 4 cups flour;
beat well.
Mix	in
remaining 2 cups flour and beat again.
Can be refrigerated,
then
let re-rise and cook at 375° until golden brown.
Roll into round shape; dip into hot butter and fold in half to make like crescent rolls.

title: cream fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar, butter, salt and marshmallows in a saucepan. Stir constantly.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in buttered pan or drop from spoon on wax paper.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix cake mix except reserved 1 cup with egg and 1/2 cup melted butter and spread on bottom of 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
In bowl, combine pumpkin, eggs, milk, sugar and pumpkin pie spice.
Mix and pour in cake pan.
Take reserved 1 cup cake mix and add 2 tablespoons melted butter, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix until crumbly and sprinkle over pumpkin.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt together.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir until it boils, then don't stir.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over 6 quarts of popped corn.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: tex-mexaroni
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in a large pot.
Add enough water so that macaroni is covered.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until macaroni is soft.
Top with cheese before serving if desired.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef; drain. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour in 13 x 9 pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix with mixer the cream cheese, butter, eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread on 2 butter crusts.
Spread the drained, crushed pineapple over the filling.
Slice the bananas over pineapple. Cover with La Creme whipped topping.
Garnish with cherries and pecans.
Top with shaved chocolate.
Chill 1 hour.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; press into large baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread on cooled crust.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except marshmallows.
Press into cookie sheet; bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover top of brownies with the marshmallows.
Return to oven until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: marinade for fish
directions: With a fork, combine olive oil and dry white wine. Add garlic cloves (finely chopped), peppercorns (crushed), salt, Worcestershire sauce and paprika.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl. Serve cold.

title: fruit cookie pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie onto ungreased pizza pan and bake (per instructions on cookie package) until done (slightly browned). Let cool.
In a medium-size bowl, generously stir cream cheese with spoon or use mixer to eliminate lumps; add strawberry yogurt and mix until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cool cookie pizza.
Cover pizza with fruit.
Just before serving, spray whipped cream on.

title: bread sticks
directions: Thaw bread and flatten in jellyroll pan.
Spread out.
Pour batter over, sprinkle with bouillon granules and then seeds. Put grated cheese on top and press down.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut as soon as you take them out of the oven.

title: six hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook at 250° for 6 hours.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops (optional).
Place rice in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Place chops over rice.
Mix soup, water and celery.
Pour over chops and rice.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peppers in sauce
directions: Slice and seed enough peppers to make 2 gallons (mix as desired).
To this, add boiling water to cover.
Let stand 5 or 10 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Cook on low for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not brown meatballs; just put in sauce and stir occasionally.

title: candied ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, combine juice from the can of pineapple, half the juice from the jar of cherries and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and set aside.
Place ham in a shallow baking pan.
Make cuts on the top and sides of ham approximately 1/4-inch deep.
Arrange pineapple slices with cherries securing with toothpicks.
Pour the juice mixture over ham.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.

title: fajitas
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate meat for 2 hours.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine all ingredients except onion.
May need to add more flour or milk depending on how thick you want it.
Slice onion into rings.
Dip into mixture and deep fry.
(Beer is good in place of or mixed with milk.)

title: peaches and cream roll
directions: Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper; grease paper with oleo.

title: nana cookies
directions: Mix sugar, egg and margarine.
Add milk and flour with soda. Shape into 2-inch roll and chill.
Cut thin.
Dip in sugar.
Place on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: christopher's peanut butter, raisin banana sandwich
directions: You take one slice of bread and you use a butter knife to smear your peanut butter all over the bread.
Then you cut your banana into six round circles.
You lay the banana circles on top of the peanut butter.
Then clump your raisins on top of that. Take the other slice of bread and push it down on everything! It's real good.
(I like mine cut into fourths.)
Yum yum.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder and add to first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix in order given.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in 2 (8 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch) E-Z Foil loaf pans, bought at Bill's Super Value.

title: beulah's french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a jar.
Keeps in a refrigerator for a long time.
Excellent over fresh fruit.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend egg, milk and oil and add to dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries. Spoon equally into lined muffin tin.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: creamette casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chipped beef rye boat dip
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a blender.
Whip until smooth and creamy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except cheese, paprika and parsley.
Toss gently until well mixed.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Sprinkle paprika on top of cheese.
Return to oven and bake another 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Remove and sprinkle with chopped parsley before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking 45 minutes.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool; frost with icing.
Cut into bars, about 3 x 1 inch.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with potato chips, if desired.

title: easy french bread
directions: Mix water, yeast, sugar and butter and let stand until bubbly (about 1/2 hour).
Add egg, salt and about 5 cups of flour, a cup at a time.
Transfer to floured surface and knead in remaining flour until smooth.
Place in an oiled bowl for an hour or more, until doubled.
Punch down dough and divide dough in half.
Shape into loaves and place in oiled loaf pans.
Let sit until double, about an hour.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 oblong loaves.

title: butterfingers
directions: Flour logs and
roll out 3 inches long; a little larger than a pencil.
Bake
at
until brown, about 15 minutes. Do not grease pan!

title: orange-glazed carrots
directions: In medium saucepan, over high heat, bring 1-inch water to boil.
Place steamer basket in saucepan; add carrots and onions. Reduce heat to medium.
Cover; steam until just tender (8 or 10 minutes).
Remove basket from saucepan; keep vegetables warm. Place orange juice, brown sugar and fennel seeds in another saucepan.
Cook about 1 minute, stirring until syrupy.
Return vegetables to this mixture and toss.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package; omit salt. Mix together soup, milk, egg, mayonnaise and cheese.
Place broccoli in a 10 x 6 1/2-inch baking dish, greased.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli.
Add dry bread crumbs that have been mixed with margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Arrange alternate layers of dry bread crumbs, applesauce and brown sugar in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of each layer.
Dot with butter; place on steamer plate and cook for 1 hour.
If desired, the pudding may be set in the oven for a few minutes to crisp the top.

title: mushroom rice ring
directions: Combine rice, water and salt; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat very low.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°. Chop mushrooms and saute in butter for 3 minutes.
Add water or bouillon.
Combine rice and mushroom mixture.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon mixture in a greased 7-inch ring mold. Set in a pan of 1-inch water; bake 30 minutes.
When done, invert on platter and fill with 2 to 3 cups cream fish or meat.

title: chicken spinach braid
directions: Boil chicken and dice.
Squeeze water out of spinach.
Combine chicken, spinach, Ricotta, Parmesan and garlic.
Arrange crescents into rectangle, pressing edges together.
Place chicken spinach filling in a roll down center of crescent rectangle.
Top with Provolone.
From mixture out, cut crescent out in strips. Alternately bring each strip up and over, forming braid.
Bake at crescent instructions.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients.
Combine sugars, oleo and eggs. Beat until creamy.
Alternately add 1 cup milk and the first 4 ingredients.
Lastly, fold in 3 1/2 cups of peeled and thinly sliced apples.
Pour batter into 2 greased 9-inch deep pie tins. Sprinkle the topping on tops before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 3/4 to 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: "you'll never believe it" rib roast
directions: Place beef in roasting
pan,
uncovered, and put in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Turn off the
oven,
but do not open the oven door at all.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter, eggs, sugar and 1 cup flour.
Use other flour to coat fruit. Add to mixture. Add nuts. Add flavoring last and bake at 275°.
Cook with a pan of water under it. Takes about 3 hours to cook. Line your ungreased tube pan with 2 layers of brown paper.

title: banana pudding(yummy)
directions: Layer bananas and wafers.
In large bowl, mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip together.
Pour over bananas and wafers.
(Makes large pudding.)

title: herb rice
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet and add onions and rice.
Stir constantly until rice and onions are yellow.
Put in rice pot and add marjoram, summer savory, rosemary and salt.
Either use chicken stock liquid or dissolve 3 chicken bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water.
Add to rice mixture.
Cook as for regular rice.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix margarine, sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix milk and pudding.
Layer, in large container, starting with crumbs, cream cheese mixture, pudding and ending with crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and lemon juice.
Add whipping cream which has been whipped fairly stiff.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust or individual pie shells.
Put in freezer in Baggie or Baggies.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put sliced pickles, pepper and onions into large bowl.
Cover with ice water; let stand for about 1 hour.
Drain.
Put into large container that will fit into your refrigerator.
Cover pickles, pepper and onions with the vinegar, sugar and spices. Mixture will stay for about 6 months in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat oil in skillet with pork (lightly seasoned with garlic salt), cut into bite size pieces.
Add pineapple and green pepper. Turn heat down to low.
When pineapple juice starts to thicken and brown, add cornstarch (into which vinegar, ketchup, soy sauce and garlic have been stirred).
When pork and pepper are fork-tender, add thickening made of 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water and stir until clear.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: marshmallow and fruit salad
directions: Mix marshmallows, sour cream and vanilla together.
Add pineapple, fruit cocktail and pecans.
Mix well; put in refrigerator a few hours before serving.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly and dry.
Wrap with foil and bake in 400° oven for about 1 hour or until tender to touch.
Unwrap and let cool 30 minutes.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out the inside, saving the hulls.

title: mexican pick-up sticks
directions: Combine French fried onions, potato sticks and cheese puffs. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter; stir to combine.
Sprinkle with taco seasoning; mix well.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes; stir every 15 minutes.

title: jennifer's macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain. Place onion and 1 tablespoon margarine in small saucepan.
Over medium heat, cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper; cook 1 minute.
Slowly stir in milk; cook, stirring until smooth.
Add 3/4 of the cheese; stir until melted.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Add soup, milk and vegetable. Place mixture into greased casserole.
Set Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water until tender.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again.
Toss with salts, onions, eggs, celery, pimento and green pepper.
Add peas and mayonnaise and mix well.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly together the first 5 ingredients.
Sift together flour and salt and stir in.
Divide into 2 halves. Blend into one-half of dough, 1/2 teaspoon of red food coloring. Roll 1 teaspoon each color dough into a strip, about 4 inches long.
Place strips, side by side; press lightly together and twist like a rope.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add onion.
Saute until tender.
Add broccoli.
Cook until broccoli separates, stirring frequently.
Stir in mushroom soup, mushrooms and cheese.
Cook over low heat for about 15 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Beat together until smooth cream cheese, sour cream and Miracle Whip.
Spoon mixture on 12-inch round serving platter (recommend platter that has a lip).
Cover with cocktail sauce. Sprinkle cheese, shrimp, onion and tomato.
Cover and chill.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Peel the pumpkins and remove the seeds.
Dice the peeled pumpkins and set aside.
In a large pot, brown the onions and garlic in the peanut oil.
Add the pumpkin, vegetable broth and optional pepper and season to taste.
Cover and cook until somewhat smooth and thick.
Mash some of the pumpkin with a wire whisk to help thicken.
Cook approximately 1 to 2 hours.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together both sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and mix until fluffy.
Add vanilla and then peanut butter.
After mixing together, slowly add flour and soda mixture.
When mixed, add your oatmeal and then pecans.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: fruited cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
Add cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Place in 2-quart mold and refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crab pate
directions: Melt gelatin in 3 tablespoons water.
Heat mushroom soup until hot, but not boiling.
Add gelatin, then cream cheese and other ingredients.
Place in mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on the package and add softened cream cheese.
Whip until smooth.
Add pineapple and juice, nuts and the marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: black bean and corn salsa
directions: Cook corn and drain. Combine corn and remaining ingredients. Makes 4 cups.

title: lemon-garlic chicken
directions: Skin chicken and trim off fat.
Wash and dry chicken.
Salt and pepper both sides.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Sprinkle each piece with a few drops of lemon juice.

title: leah's peach cobbler
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 12 inch pan.
Pour peaches into pan. Mix together sugar and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Melt butter and pour over sugar and peaches.
Cover top with pie crust, torn into pieces.
Bake at 325 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish. Add all ingredients. Heat until shrimp turn pink. Place in preheated oven to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate mint chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and egg and mix well.
Mix flour, cocoa and soda; stir dry mixture into first mixture.
Add chocolate morsels and nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 375°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: my sister's pot roast
directions: *Amount depends on your family and taste.

title: bagel cheese dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 24 hours. Arrange on a tray with cut up rye or wheat bagels and enjoy.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple; mix juice with pudding until dissolved and then fold in remaining ingredients and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease a large ovenproof bowl.
Pour the pineapple into the prepared bowl.
Combine the sugar and flour and sprinkle over the pineapple.
Sprinkle the grated cheese over the pineapple, then the cracker crumbs.
Pour the butter over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn(excellent)
directions: Cut off about 4 inches from the top of a large brown paper bag.
Place popped corn in the bag.
Sprinkle the nuts over the popcorn (don't shake the bag; nuts should rest on top of popped corn).

title: greek salad
directions: Wash and prepare all the vegetables.
Combine in a large bowl and add the anchovies, olives and cheese.
Toss well with your favorite Italian dressing or:

title: seafood parisienne
directions: Cook artichoke hearts as directed on package. Drain and place in 3-quart ovenproof casserole. Stir in rice and shrimp.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour into casserole.
Cover and bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until most of the liquid has been absorbed. Stir before serving. Garnish with lemon wedges, if desired. Serves 8.

title: giant cinnamon twist bread
directions: About 6 hours before serving:
In large bowl combine yeast, salt, 2 cups flour and 1 cup sugar.
In 1-quart saucepan over low heat, heat milk and 1 cup butter or margarine until very warm (120° to 130°).
(Butter or margarine does not need to melt completely.) With mixer at low speed, gradually pour liquid into dry ingredients.
Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Beat in 2 eggs and 2 cups flour; continue beating 2 minutes.
With wooden spoon, stir in enough additional flour (about 3 cups) to make a soft dough. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
In necessary, add more flour while kneading.
Shape dough into bowl, turning over so that top of dough is greased.
Cover bowl with towel; let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) away from draft, until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour once and measure; add baking powder and sift again. Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream.
Add beaten egg, then flour alternately with milk; beat.
In heavy skillet, melt 4 tablespoons butter; add 1 cup brown sugar.
Stir until melted. Add batter over skillet covered with pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Do Not Cook Noodles.
Spray a 9 1/2 inch x 13 inch pan with Pam.
Then put some meat sauce on the bottom, then a layer of noodles, a layer of cottage cheese, a layer of each of the Colby cheese, a layer of mozzarella cheese.
Continue to make layers until all of sauce, cottage cheese and other cheeses are used up, making sure there is a layer of Colby and mozzarella cheese on top. Sprinkle this with parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil (that has been sprayed with Pam).
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Take foil off for last 15 minutes of baking.

title: coleslaw(for freezer)
directions: Add 2 cups sugar and boil 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm and pour over cabbage.
Place in containers and freeze.
This is much better after it is frozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, Crisco and brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add bacon strips on top.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: rice balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except herb seasoning and refrigerate. Put herb seasoning in food processor and blend until smooth. Roll rice in small balls. Pour herb seasoning on aluminum foil. Roll rice balls to cover all in seasoning. Deep fry balls until golden brown. These balls can be frozen.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups water.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg. Add yeast to mixture; add flour and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Make 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Pare, core and quarter apples, then halve crosswise to make chunks.
(You should have about 7 cups.)

title: edible wreaths
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter in a large saucepan.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and food coloring.
Carefully stir in cornflakes until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Shape into wreaths; decorate with red hots to make berries.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: For your crust, mix vanilla wafers, pecans and melted margarine.
Press 3/4 of mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan and set in freezer.
Now set out your ice cream to soften.
Melt your chocolate chips and set aside.
In a medium bowl beat powdered sugar and margarine together; add eggs.
Mix together with melted chocolate.
Pour on top of your wafer mix, evenly.
Then spoon ice cream evenly.
Add your remaining crust.

title: snow paint
directions: Mix. Makes enough for 8 to 10 children.
Beat with mixer until consistency of frosting.
It may be applied with fingers to construction paper and sprinkled with glitter.
Suds mixed in the morning will be good during the day.

title: crab and water chestnut spread
directions: Chop crab meat and combine with water chestnuts, soy sauce, mayonnaise and onions.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Serve with sliced fruits and berries.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mash bananas.
Add flour, sugar, butter and nutmeg.
Pour into buttered, 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until delicately browned on top.
Cut into squares and serve hot or cold, dusted with powdered sugar.
Can use whipped cream, if desired.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Mix eggs, raisins and vanilla; let stand at least 1 hour. Cream shortening and sugars.
Stir in raisin mixture.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; add to sugar-raisin mixture and blend well.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts (dough will be stiff).
Roll into small balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Tenderize chicken with mallet to about 1/2-inch thick.
Lay on piece of ham and thin slice of cheese. Roll up and hold with toothpick.
Dip each in egg or milk, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in glass dish and bake about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vessie's baked pineapple
directions: Drain juice of pineapple into a saucepan.
Arrange pineapple slices in a shallow baking dish.
Put a marshmallow in each pineapple hole.
Heat the pineapple juice (about 1 cup) to boiling point then add the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the pineapple slices.
Put into a 350° oven about 10 to 15 minutes or until the marshmallows are melted and brown.

title: bacon potato puffs
directions: Cut bacon in half; wrap around 1 potato puff. Place on paper plate with plenty of paper towels (to soak up grease). You can put 6 or 7 on one plate. Cover with paper towel. Cook in microwave 4 to 5 minutes. Serve right away or reheat in oven.

title: primavara contadina
directions: In medium skillet heat oil.
Saute onion and garlic for one minute.
Add zucchini, yellow squash and bell pepper.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in reserved tomato juice, Italian
paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes and basil.
Simmer for 1 minute. Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Serve sauce over pasta.
Garnish with olives and basil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: mushroom cups
directions: Cut bread in 3-inch circles; butter one side.
Put in small muffin pans, buttered side down.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Cook mushrooms 3 minutes; drain.
Sprinkle flour over mushrooms; stir completely.
Add half and half.
Stir until it boils and thickens. Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Fill cups; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then eat.
May be frozen too.

title: peanut butter snacks
directions: Lay pecan halves on foil-lined pan.
Cover with 3 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle salt to taste.
Put in 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Leave in oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours with door closed.

title: coffee nut tortoni
directions: Whip cream; fold in 1/4 cup sugar, instant coffee and flavorings. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form and gradually add 2 tablespoons sugar and beat to stiff peaks. Mix nuts and coconut. Fold egg whites into whipped cream. Spoon into metal ice cube tray; cover with nuts and coconut. Freeze.

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix well and let stand overnight.

title: corn moussaka
directions: Spread corn in ungreased baking dish.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add flour.
Cook and stir one minute.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic salt and cinnamon.
Spread ground beef mixture over corn and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Mix together poppy seed, onion, margarine, mustard and Worcestershire sauce over low heat.
Spread 1/2 of mixture over bottom of roll.
Layer ham and cheese; spread remaining mixture on top of roll.
Heat at 300° for about 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: cherry slurpee
directions: Pour 1 cup of club soda in a blender. Add the sugar, Kool-Aid mix and cherry extract. Blend until all sugar is dissolved. Add crushed ice and blend on high speed until the drink is a slushy smooth consistency with no chunks of ice. Add the remaining club soda and blend until mixed.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Place in large bowl in order (except noodles, mayonnaise and salt and pepper).
Cover with lid and allow to set at least 1 hour. This results in vegetables being crisp.
When ready to serve, add Chinese noodles and toss with mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste. Be sure to mix well.
Can be served with French and butter as main dish.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Cook 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together water and oats and cover.
Cream together butter and both sugars.
Sift together flour, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add to batter mixture and mix well.
Stir in oatmeal mixture. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until springy.

title: cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound meat until 1/4-inch thick.
Place one slice each of ham and cheese in center of each piece.
Roll up, beginning at narrow end.
Secure with wooden picks.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Coat rolls in mixture and then dip into egg.
Then roll in bread crumbs. Fry in oil until brown. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Cream sugar and salad oil; add pumpkin and eggs.
Next add flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Pour into 18 x 12 x1-inch jelly roll pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: fat free oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla until well blended.
Add raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes.

title: omelet souffle
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Beat the eggs (white) to a stiff froth.
Beat the yolks and the sugar to a cream, add the lemon juice, orange flower water or Kirsch.
Add whites of the eggs.
Stir carefully and heap all quickly into the baking dish and bake about 15 minutes, until top is a delicate brown.
Serve immediately as it will fall if allowed to stand.
May serve as a dessert.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Pour melted butter, sugar and cinnamon over it.
Place pie filling into baking dish and top with bread mixture.
Bake in oven at 400° until golden brown. Cool and serve.

title: chicken and peppers
directions: In medium bowl, combine soy sauce, sherry, ginger and chicken. Marinate several hours.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Blend well.
Chill until partially set.
Add pecans.
Pour into mold and chill to firm.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 3 minutes at high speed.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; add to mixture, alternating with milk.
Add cocoa paste.
Pour into greased baking pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese beef log
directions: Combine first three ingredients; mix well.
Chop beef into small pieces.
Roll cheese mixture into a log and roll in beef pieces, covering well.

title: black magic cake
directions: Melt shortening, them mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together and form 1 loaf.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Boil eggs.
While macaroni is cooking, cut up in teeny, tiny pieces:
radishes, carrots, bell pepper, cucumber, tomatoes and onion.
Put these teeny, tiny pieces in a small bowl and set aside.

title: granny's strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake bakes,
dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.

title: italian style pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Add remaining ingredients to chops.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: jack-o'-lantern cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. Prepare cake per directions on package.
Measure 1/4 cup frosting into small bowl and tint with the green food coloring.
Frost the cone and put in refrigerator.
Tint remaining frosting with red and yellow to desired color of orange.
Measure 3 tablespoons of orange frosting and add green color to make brown frosting.
Frost cake with orange frosting and decorate face of Jack-O'-Lantern with the brown.
Place green frosted ice cream cone in center hole of cake to make stem.

title: flakes pancakes
directions: Prepare pancake mix as directed on package using the amount of milk or water specified.
Add crushed cereal and 1/2 cup milk or water.
Using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake, bake on hot griddle until bubbly on top.
Turn to brown other side.
Makes about 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: oven barbecued steak
directions: Cut meat into 10 serving pieces.
In large skillet, brown meat in oil over medium heat.
Remove to Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet; simmer 5 minutes.
Pour ketchup mixture over meat.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.
(Excellent with venison.)

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix well the cream cheese and sugar. Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas. Fold in Cool Whip. Place in freezer. Remove 30 minutes before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put frozen potatoes in covered dish and add soup.
Stir.
Cook in oven 45 minutes, then add cheese to top.
Cook 10 more minutes.
If you want a more crispy top, let the lid off for the last 10 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: clam puffs
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together, except paprika.
Spread on toasted bread rounds or crackers and put in broiler for a few minutes until puffy.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve piping hot. Makes 20 puffs.

title: spaghetti sauce for meatballs
directions: Fry onion and garlic into olive oil and cook until tender in a large pot. Add tomato paste and cook a while. Then add pureed tomatoes. Add all other ingredients and cook. Add your meatballs into sauce and cook 2 hours, stirring often.

title: cream cheese crescent rolls
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Press 1 can crescent rolls into pan (room temperature).

title: pork chops with kraut and apples(do ahead)
directions: Combine sauerkraut, chives and dill weed.
Arrange in bottom of shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.

title: yummy oatmeal apple squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray Pam spray on a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Combine liquid Butter Buds, brown sugar and granulated sugar in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in Egg Beaters, apple juice and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until blended.
Stir in oats, apples and raisins with a spoon.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on cooling rack.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: tuna slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: oyster dressing
directions: In a large bowl crush up crackers.
Put in onion, sage and pepper.
Stir in oysters.
Add liquid from oysters.
Mix in essence.
Mix well.
May be a little sloppy.
May need more essence.
Put in greased baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake in oven at 425° until oysters are bubbly about 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: blueberry or apple muffins
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full before baking.

title: snakemeat
directions: Marinate in store bought or homemade Italian salad dressing. Chill at least 8 hours.
You may want to strain out some of the dressing before serving.
Serve cold with tostado chips.
The fun of this is to take it to a party and announce after 3/4 of the bowl is gone that the black olives are "snakemeat".
You'll be surprised at the reactions you get.

title: sandies
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar, water and vanilla. Stir flour into mixture and add nuts. Chill for 2 hours. Shape into round balls. Bake in a 325° oven about 20 minutes. When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: butter mochi
directions: In a bowl, mix mochiko and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and coconut milk.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and baking powder.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with the melted butter.
Pour any extra butter into the batter and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until light brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake until brown in 9 inch iron skillet.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Cream together butter and the 1/2 cup sugar. Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Stir in vanilla and flour, mixing well.
Spread evenly in buttered 9-inch round cake pan.
Place apple wedges into cake batter to form a circular pattern.
Mix together 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over cake. Sprinkle top with almonds. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: miss scarlett's chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In large pot, add ground beef, onion, garlic, chili powder, cayenne pepper and salt.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer on low heat, covered, 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bake 1 pie crust as directed on box in a deep pie dish. Mix deboned chicken, Veg-All
and
the
soup.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with
other
unbaked
pie crust.
Press fork around edges of pie crust and
make a few slits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until top pie crust is done.

title: salmon marinade yuka style
directions: Cut salmon into bite-sized pieces and rinse with water and salt.
