Lightly cover salmon with cornstarch and fry in hot oil. In a deep container, lay salmon, vegetables, and lemon on top. Pour marinade over top.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Bring the butter and sugar to a boil for about a minute.
Line a jelly roll pan with crackers.
Pour the boiled sugar and butter over crackers.
May sprinkle with fine nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Take out of pan immediately and put on wax paper.

title: refrigerator hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Let rise in container.
In a large bowl, combine hot water, 1/3 cup sugar, oil and salt.
Cool and add yeast mixture, egg and flour.
Blend well. Oil top of dough and cover with dry cloth to let double in bulk. Mash down and knead on flour covered board.
Shape into rolls and let rise.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for a week.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until just tender.
Cool.
Boil eggs until hard-boiled; peel and cut in half.
Remove yolk to blender jar.
Peel and cut potatoes into 1/3-inch dice and put into large bowl.
Add celery, onion, cucumber, parsley, salt, pepper, relish and chopped egg whites.
Add mayonnaise, mustard and juice to the yolks and blend until smooth.
Add to potato mixture; blend well, cover and chill.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onion and green pepper; drain.
Cook medium noodles.
Drain and add salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish. Mix in mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese soup and Pet milk.
Place in oven until warm.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and spread with butter or margarine. Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and set aside.

title: sweet 'n sour rice
directions: Prepare 3 cups rice according to package directions (approximately 6 cups cooked).

title: breaded cauliflower
directions: Boil small head of cauliflower in salted water for about 10 minutes.
Cut up into little florets.
Put in flour, then in beaten egg and then flour again.
Fry in hot oil and brown on each side.
May deep-fry.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place chops in casserole.
Cover with chopped onion, chopped green pepper and rice.
Over all pour the undiluted tomato soup. Cook in slow oven (200°) for 2 hours or longer.
An ideal dish to use when you plan to be out until late afternoon.
Good served with white beans, applesauce or fried apples and cornbread.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with sugar, flour and cheese.
Top with crackers and pour melted butter over it.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: homemade freezer ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Lastly add the 1/2 gallon milk.
When partially frozen any fruit may be added.

title: tuna pie
directions: Mix and pour in shell.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°. Can add cooked broccoli or mushrooms or zucchini.
I add broccoli.

title: stina bars
directions: Spray large jelly roll pan with Pam cooking spray.
Line with foil.
Spray foil with Pam.
Line foil with crackers (single layer).
Melt butter and brown sugar in saucepan until well blended.
Bring to boil stirring constantly; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in soda.
Spread over crackers evenly (may have to press crackers back down).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Spread chocolate chips over and let stand until melted.
Spread with back of spoon over pan evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Melt butter; add cake mix and 1 egg.
Press into long pan. Cream the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar together; pour over cake mix layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: casserole
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except eggs.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Stir in the diced eggs.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
(Recipe may be doubled or tripled).

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Fold milk into Cool Whip, then fold in other ingredients in order listed.
Chill for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in egg, 1 tablespoon granulated sugar and the baking mix; beat vigorously.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 20 times.
Roll into rectangle, 16 x 9-inch; spread with butter and sprinkle with mixture of 1/3 cup sugar, the raisins and cinnamon.
Roll up, beginning at the wide side.
Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal.
With seam side down, shape dough into ring on greased baking sheet; pinch ends together.
With scissors, make cuts 2/3 of the way through ring at 1-inch intervals.
Turn each section on its side.
Let rise in a warm place about 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken in crock-pot and debone.
Simmer the soup with the green chilies until smooth.
May need to add a little water to soup mixture.

title: brenda's potato soup
directions: Place butter, onion, potatoes and water into a saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil until potatoes are done.
Do not overcook.
Then add soup, milk, salt, pepper and Cheez Whiz.
Heat until warmed through.
Add bacon last.

title: meat ball bites
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into bite size balls.
Bake on cookie sheet in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Serve hot with party picks.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Fix
macaroni as directed on box.
Brown hamburger with onions.
Salt
and pepper to taste.
Layer macaroni, hamburger and sauce in casserole dish.
Mix mushrooms in with hamburger after it
is
browned.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until
hot through.
Sometimes I mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.

title: vidalia onion-cranberry relish
directions: Cook onion in butter in a medium skillet for 10 minutes or till tender, stirring frequently.
Add wine and salt.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, and 1 cup water in a medium saucepan; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add 2 cups cranberries and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining cranberries; cook 10 minutes more or till berries pop, stirring frequently.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Stir in onion mixture. Transfer to a medium bowl.
Cover and chill until serving time or up to 3 days.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain and save juice from pineapple.
Combine pineapple, marshmallows and pecans in bowl and set aside.
In small saucepan, combine pineapple juice, vinegar, sugar, cornstarch, butter and egg; cook over medium heat until smooth and thickened.
When sauce has cooled, pour over pineapple mixture and chill several hours. Just before serving, fold in whipped cream.
Serve cold.

title: blueberry muffins(makes 12 muffins.)
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add blueberries.
Add milk, melted butter and egg.
Mix until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon batter into paper-lined microsafe baking or cupcake pan.
Microwave at Medium-high power for 3 minutes.
Let rest for 3 minutes. Microwave at High power for another 2 minutes or until muffins are done.
Serve them warm with butter or honey.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Split chicken in half with poultry shears, cutting through the breastbone.
Place chicken, skin side up, on counter and press down firmly to crack back bones so that chicken lies flat.
Loosen skin over top of chicken, using fingers and a sharp paring knife. Mix Ricotta cheese, garlic, spinach and herbs.
Stuff mixture evenly under skin over breast of chicken.
Brush skin of chicken lightly with oil; sprinkle with
paprika.
Place chicken on rack in roasting pan; bake at 350° until chicken is golden and juices run clear when the thickest part of the thigh is pierced, about 1 1/4 hours.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: miniature bacon-cheese quiche
directions: Combine all 8 ingredients; stir well.
Pour into prepared Pastry Shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk to remove large lumps.
Add oil and next 3 ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: upside-down cherry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in cake pan.
Mix baking powder, flour, milk and salt.
Pour this mixture over oleo in the cake pan.
Pour cherries on top.
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: meat roll
directions: Combine beef and veal, egg and 1 teaspoon salt. Mix well.
Pat into rectangular shape. Mix bread crumbs, onion, celery, parsley, dash of salt, raisins, sage and milk.
Spread over meat.
Roll as you would a jelly roll. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add beaten eggs and coconut extract. Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately. Add coconut last. Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for an hour.

title: mystery salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large bowl.
Garnish with more nuts, if desired. Cover and refrigerate until served.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, onion, mushrooms and eggs in large bowl.
In a small mixing bowl; combine oil, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and spices, mix well.
(This makes extra dressing mix that can be use later for other salads. Keep in refrigerator.) Add dressing mix; and top with tomatoes, garlic croutons (if desired) and bacon.

title: jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage; drain and cut in bite size pieces.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in drippings until tender.
Add broth, tomatoes, seasoning, chicken and sausage.
Bring to a boil and add rice. Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add shrimp during last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Crumble up heath bars (leave candy bars in wrapper and beat them with a hammer).

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Combine soup, milk, sour cream and chillies.
Stir to blend.
Boil and simmer until ready to use.

title: strata
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Grease well a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add mixture.
Chill 12 hours or overnight.
Cook for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: crispy chocolate bars
directions: In large saucepan, combine chocolate and butterscotch morsels and peanut butter. Stir over low heat until smooth. Remove from heat. Add corn flakes. Stir until mixed. Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan that's been sprayed with cooking spray. Cut when cool.

title: martha's four alarm chili
directions: Brown hamburger and saute onion in it.
Combine rest of ingredients in separate pot and simmer.
Drain hamburger mix when browned and add to liquids.
May need to thin with water to reach desired consistency.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter and cook
onions
in
it until tender.
Add flour and cook 1
minute
until
thick.
Stir
in
broth
and broccoli. Bring to a
boil
and
reduce heat and simmer until broccoli is tender.
Stir in half and half and just cook until heated through. Serves 2 to 4.

title: apple fruit salad
directions: Wash apples and grapes. Peel apples and cut into small pieces. Mix ingredients in large bowl. Stir in salad dressing.

title: light and creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, pudding (dry) and spice. Beat until well blended. Fold in 2 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Top with remaining topping.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add flour.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pie crust.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's potato salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and add chopped, cooked potatoes. Make it wet because potatoes take it up.
If you need more, mix more milk and vinegar and add.
Toss carefully!

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Add cooked, well drained Italian sausage to a large steam-jacketed kettle; add onions and celery and cook until tender.
Add chicken stock to the mixture and bring to a boil. Stir in tomatoes and all other ingredients with the exception of the tortellini and the zucchini.
The tortellini are added to the soup frozen during the last 45 minutes of cooking.
Return soup to a boil, tortellini will float when cooked.
Reduce heat; add the zucchini and top with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: dorothy's potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes and boil until soft.
Add cream cheese (softened).
Beat well.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well. Place in casserole and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
May be placed in refrigerator overnight, then baked for 1 hour at 350°.
These potatoes are very delicious.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers.
Clean and steam or microwave peppers (approximately 3 minutes).
Make macaroni and cheese with milk and butter according to box directions.
Then simply stuff macaroni and cheese in peppers, sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake or microwave for another 2 minutes.
(When serving to kids, cut into bite size pieces.)

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small pan, melt 1 cup butter.
Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. In a large pot, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture; beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).
Bake 15 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
In a small pan, melt remaining 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in powdered sugar and nuts.
Spread over warm cake.

title: herbed olive oil
directions: Any oil can be flavored with a single herb or a complex mixture of herbs, spices and citrus.
If you use garlic, remove it after 2 weeks as it will overpower the other flavors.
These ingredients make a nice combination.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Bring peppers, sugar and vinegar to a hard rolling boil. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Skim off foam.
Mix in Certo.
Add a few drops of food coloring.
Pour in jars with screw top or cover with paraffin.
Serve with cream cheese or Wheat Thins, Triscuits or cracker of your choice.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugars in mixing bowl.
Add egg and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in oatmeal, vanilla and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cabbage rolls with meat
directions: Boil 1 head of cabbage until fairly soft.
Make rolls with cabbage.
Combine ground beef and Minute rice and shape to fit cabbage rolls.
Place in pan and cover with tomatoes and tomato soup.
Bake in oven for 45 to 50 minutes, basting often with juice.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water.
Bring to a boil. Drain liquid.
Place chicken cubes in the water.
Cook noodles in the chicken bouillon water.
Saute onion in butter.
In a saucepan heat milk, add cheese and melt.
Add seasonings.
Mix everything together and serve.
Makes a large pot of soup.
This is very good.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Combine pineapple and gelatin in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool completely.
Add buttermilk and nuts; fold in whipped topping.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes about 16 to 18 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *May use chicken thighs instead for more flavor.

title: bran flax muffins
directions: Mix together flour, flax seed meal, oat bran, brown sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl. Stir in carrots, apples, raisins (if desired) and nuts.
Combine milk, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Stir until ingredients are moistened.
Do not over mix.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 15 medium muffins.

title: gerry's cornbread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar into a large mixing bowl and stir, mixing thoroughly with fork.
Add cornmeal.
Stir again.
Add milk and eggs, stir with fork until well blended.
Grease baking dish.
Pour in mixture and bake at 400° until well brown on top, approximately 30 to 35 minutes. Should be firm on top if pressed with fork when done.
Do not use electric mixer.

title: spiced tea
directions: Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to cup boiling water.
Also delicious as iced tea.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and flour.
Stir in butter; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture and press the rest into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 or 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese with sugar.
Add egg, lemon juice, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour over baked crust.
Top with reserved mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Chill and cut into squares to serve.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients together. Chill. Serve with sliced Granny Smith apples.

title: all eats meatballs
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put turkey, chicken, beef, onion, cooked rice and celery.
Mix well.
Add soup mix, egg, chili seasoning, flour and bread crumbs to the meat mixture.
Mix well. Add another egg, if too dry, at this point.
Roll out in 1 to 2-inch meatballs.
Cook on baking sheet at 350° for 1 hour (according to size of meatballs).
Add to your favorite sauce. Serves 5 to 6.

title: oniony cube steaks
directions: Bread cube steaks with flour and seasoned salt.
Brown in Crisco until almost done.
Lay cube steaks out in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour over cube steaks the onion soup.

title: country cole slaw
directions: Chop or shred cabbage.
Combine with onions and green pepper in large bowl.
Mix other ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Toss lightly.
Cover.
Chill 4 hours.
Makes 6 (3/4 cup) servings).

title: peach bread
directions: Mix ingredients and add crushed peaches.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake for 1 hour in oven (do not preheat) at 300°.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix dates, soda and boiling water together and cool.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and black walnuts.
Add date mixture to batter.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell. Mix together jello, sugar and cornstarch. Then add warm water and red food coloring.
Cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add sliced strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell.
When set, top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chili soup
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling, stirring occasionally.
If you wish, garnish soup with corn chips.

title: sausage, chili and cheese tartlets
directions: Cook sausage in large heavy skillet over medium-high heat until no longer pink, breaking up with a fork.
Drain off fat. Add salsa, cheeses and green chilies to skillet and simmer until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: potatoes in mustard sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt oleo in small pan; add onion. Cook over medium heat until onion is translucent.
Whisk in flour and bouillon in water.
Add mustard and pepper; cook, stirring until thick.
Spray shallow baking dish with Pam.
Spread potatoes in dish.
Pour sauce evenly over top.
Sprinkle evenly with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake until lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: orange honey butter
directions: Beat until light and fluffy.
Serve over pancakes, waffles, muffins, gingerbread or French toast.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: raisin nut cookies
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil.
Do not drain.
Mix the dry ingredients together.
Cream the butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Add raisin mixture and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad with cooked dressing
directions: Combine sugar and flour in saucepan.
Combine beaten egg and fruit juices; gradually blend with flour-sugar mixture.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and cool. Fold in bananas, apples and pineapple.
Put into a dish; garnish with strawberries or cherries.
Cover and chill.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Pour in milk all at once.
Stir with fork until dough forms ball.
Dump dough on floured countertop.
Knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll dough into oblong sheet about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread dough with softened butter.
Sprinkle with a mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 450°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken pie
directions: Lightly brown chicken in skillet.
Place in casserole dish. Add chopped boiled eggs.
Mix chicken broth and both soups.
Pour over chicken.
Add vegetables.
Mix melted margarine, milk and flour.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.

title: honey banana muffins(2 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven and spray muffin tins.
Sift and mix well the dry ingredients.
Mix well the liquid ingredients and add to the dry ingredients all at once.
DO NOT OVERMIX!
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Notice oven temperature is lower than most muffins as honey will burn easier.
May add nuts.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: fish patties
directions: Bring pot of water to full boil (enough to cover fish).
Drop in fish.
Leave only until rawness is out and fish turns white. Drain fish; season while still warm.
Break into small pieces.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place in well oiled casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Very good!

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook the head; after all surplus fat has been removed, put through food chopper.
Add other ingredients and cook until tender.
Can while hot in sterilized jars.

title: spoon bread
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour into melted margarine.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Top with Cheddar cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: irish stew
directions: Trim fat from mutton and cut meat into pieces.

Put into a saucepan and add just enough water to cover meat. Cook, covered, 1 1/2 hours on medium heat. Cut onions into quarters. Cut carrots and cabbage into strips and quarter the potatoes. Cover the bottom of a large heatproof casserole with slices of bacon. Cover with alternate layers of mutton, onions, carrots, cabbage and potatoes. Season layers with remaining ingredients.
Pour over all enough mutton broth to barely cover the top layer.
Bring to a boil. Cover tightly and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender. Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: *Could use turkey instead of chicken.

title: quiche
directions: Cook broccoli and onions; drain.
Beat eggs, cream and Mrs. Dash.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into the baked pie shells.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Let cool 15 minutes.

title: pina colada coconut cake
directions: Make and bake cake following directions on box.
While cake is hot, mix condensed milk and Coco Lopez.
Punch holes in cake and pour mixture over cake.
Let cake cool.
Mix coconut and Cool Whip.
Spread over cake.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: lime salad
directions: Follow directions on Jello box for molded gelatin.
Blend sour cream with jello.
Add pineapple and nuts, Pour into mold and refrigerate.
Stir mixture occasionally until thick to keep pineapple and nuts from setting on top.

title: potato gratin with boursin
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Butter a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with 2 inch high sides. Stir whipping cream and Boursin cheese in heavy large saucepan over medium heat until cheese melts and mixture is smooth. Arrange 1/2 of sliced potatoes in baking dish in slightly overlapping rows. Generously season potatoes in dish with salt and pepper. Pour 1/2 of cheese mixture over potatoes. Arrange remaining potatoes in slightly overlapping rows atop potatoes in dish. Generously season with salt and pepper. Pour remaining cheese mixture over potatoes. Bake until top is golden brown and potatoes are tender when pierced with a knife, about 1 hour. Sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley and serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
To drippings, add potatoes, celery and onion, salt, pepper and thyme and liquid from clams.
Heat to boiling and cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and milk and add to vegetable mixture.
Heat over medium heat until mixture thickens, stirring occasionally.
Stir in clams; heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel skin off eggplant.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip the eggplant into the beaten egg, then into the flour, coating both sides.
In a large skillet, cook eggplant in hot oil 4 to 6 minutes, flipping so that each side is golden brown.
Place eggplant slices in a single layer in a baking dish.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese, then pour over the spaghetti sauce and cheese. Place in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked beef tenderloin with vegetables(16 servings)
directions: Marinate the tenderloin overnight in the combined soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and garlic. Before cooking, add the remaining ingredients to the pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour mix in 9-inch pan.
Microwave uncovered for 6 to 8 minutes on High until edges are set.
Then for 4 to 6 minutes until center is set.
Then let cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil.
Beat until light and fluffy. Stir in pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into pumpkin mixture.
Add seedless raisins and nuts.
Blend well.
Spoon batter into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Stir in melted chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with mixer for 5 minutes after each addition or until the sugar is completely dissolved.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream. Chill.

title: baked blue fish
directions: Place bluefish fillets in a shallow ceramic or enameled baking dish.
Combine vinegar, onion, peppercorns and allspice.
Pour over fillets.
Marinate at room temperature skin side up for 1 hour. Pour off vinegar, but not onion or spices.
Turn skin side down and spread top with sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Yield:
6 servings. Carbohydrate 3 g, protein 46 g, fat 14 g, calories 330.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Stuff dates with pecans and place in a greased casserole. Beat together the eggs; add sugar, flour, salt, lemon extract and cream.
Pour over dates and dot top with butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: crab salad
directions: Boil macaroni and let cool.
Add crab, peas and onions.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, juice, salt and pepper together and pour over other ingredients.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, taco seasoning and sour cream. Spread on pizza pan or plate. Top with lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and onions. Serve with nacho chips.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Cook over hot (not boiling) water, stirring constantly until mixture coats metal spoon.
Add softened gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Cool until partially set.
Beat 3/4 cup sugar into egg whites.
Fold into custard.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill.
Use graham cracker shell.

title: hot holiday drink
directions: Heat all the ingredients and serve.

title: deer hash
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch pieces.
Boil for 4 hours or until shredded.
Add 1/4-inch cubed potatoes and chopped onion.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are tender, but still firm.

title: glaze for baked ham
directions: Mix in large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over ham and bake.
Baste frequently.

title: oven stew
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in casserole.
Sprinkle with tapioca and salt and pepper.
Pour tomatoes on top.
Bake at 250° for 6 hours, at 275° for 5 hours and at 300° for 4 hours.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: chocolate pudding pie
directions: Combine and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: hopscotch
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in double boiler and stir in peanut butter.
Mix noodles and marshmallows in a large mixing bowl; add butterscotch mixture and mix thoroughly.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill until set.
Makes about 30.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone.
Cut up tortillas in strips (2-inches). Drop into boiling chicken broth.
Stir in cream of chicken soup.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Stir the first six ingredients well; will be stiff.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: prune squares
directions: Cook prunes, 3/4 cup sugar and water together until tender. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream butter, gradually adding 1 cup of sugar; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Press 3 cups of this mixture in bottom and halfway up sides of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Spread prune mixture over crust and sprinkle rest of crumbs over top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Top with whipped cream.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, melted butter and one egg.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Next, beat together 2/3 package of 10x sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Spread on top of nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat soup, mushrooms and margarine and stir until well blended.
Drain asparagus, peas, bean sprouts and sliced water chestnuts.
Layer vegetables in order in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour soup mixture over all the vegetables.
Top with 1 can onion rings and a thin layer of crushed cheese crackers.
Heat 30 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: carefree casserole - chicken
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, water and milk in saucepan; bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon half into baking dish.
Spoon rice over vegetables.
Layer chicken over rice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Top with remaining vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spicy peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and spices in boiling water.
Stir in peach syrup and vinegar.
Chill until thickened.
Add peaches. Stir occasionally while thickening to distribute spices.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter; add paprika and stir until blended.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Simmer until tender, then add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Boil 5 minutes.
Place shrimp in this mixture and cook slowly 20 minutes.
Serve hot over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple rolls
directions: Melt butter.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk, melted butter, 6 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, egg and whole wheat flour.
Knead the dough until smooth and elastic.
Let rise in a warm place for about 40 minutes.
Punch down.
Peel apples and cut into wedges.

title: holiday punch
directions: Blend together and heat in crock-pot or electric coffee urn. Also great cold.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine hamburg, onion, rice, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix water and half the tomato sauce into mixture.
Shape into small balls.
Layer in a baking pan.
Pour remaining water and sauce over meatballs.
Cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white onion sauce
directions: Melt fat.
Add flour and finely chopped onions.
Cook until pale yellow.
Add cold stock, stirring constantly.
Stir in caraway seed.
Bring sauce to a boil and cook for 10 minutes over low heat.
Mash and season with salt.
Add vinegar and sugar, if desired.

title: bacon cheeseburger
directions: Mix ground beef with bacon, cheese, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 patties about 1-inch thick.
Pan fry in bacon drippings. Serves 4.

title: macaroni salad
directions: *Can use tuna, turkey or ham instead of chicken.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Mix all ingredients except poppy seed.
Fill 1/3 to 1/2 full and top with poppy seed.
Bake on 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add 2 eggs and mix well.
Then mix in the flour and baking soda.
Add walnuts.
Shape into rolls 2 or 3 inches in diameter.
Make 2 or 3 rolls.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake in a 350° oven 15 minutes or until light brown.
Yields about 8 dozen cookies.

title: baked pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using sharp knife, make 4 deep holes in pork and stuff with the garlic.
Season the roast with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with dried mint, pressing it into the meat. Place roast in a roasting pan with a rack.
Mix water and wine together and pour around roast.
Cover and bake until almost done, about 2 hours, basting occasionally.
Sprinkle green onions over the top and cook, uncovered, until brown.

title: crock-pot steak and rice
directions: Cook thawed steaks 3 hours on high setting.
Just put a little water in at the start.
Remove steaks from crock-pot.
Cook rice on stove top according to directions; put into crock-pot. Sprinkle salt and pepper in to taste.
Add brown gravy.
Put steaks back in pot and let warm.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: roast
directions: Use no salt. Wrap tight in foil. Cook at 250 degrees for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: beef and rice dinner
directions: Cook onion and peppers in microwave until tender. Brown beef until done.
Drain grease off. Combine salt, molasses and mustard. Add to ground beef mixture. Add tomatoes and 1 cup uncooked rice. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: veggie tuna salad
directions: Squeeze excess moisture out of the thawed tofu and crumble it.
Mix with the vegetables.
Stir together the mayonnaise, tamari, lemon juice and kelp powder in a small bowl.
Add this mixture to the tofu and vegetables and mix well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough 1/4-inch thick and layer in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Mix together cream cheese and sugar. Spread on cooled cookie crust.
Next, add cherry pie filling, sliced bananas and drained fruit cocktail.

title: johnny m. casserole
directions: Brown meat; stir in mix, then tomato paste and water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook macaroni in boiling salt water; drain.
Stir in macaroni, corn and 1 cup cheese into meat mixture.
Then put into a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice and beans
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Set aside.
Chop garlic, onion and zucchini into small pieces.
Fry garlic, onion and zucchini in hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain mushrooms and add to frypan.
Drain and rinse beans and add to frypan.
Mix cooked rice in with vegetables.
Top with your favorite sauce (soy, sweet and sour) or cheese.

title: marinated in honey, rosemary and orange(6 servings)
directions: Combiner rosemary and orange peel in large bowl. Using wooden spoon, press down on mixture to release oils. Add olive oil, honey, orange juice, lemon juice and garlic. Season with salt and pepper. Add pork, stirring to coat with marinade. Cover; chill at least 2 hours and up to 4 hours.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all together in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: quick tortellini soup(excellent)
directions: Heat oil in stock pot over medium heat; add pancetta (or Canadian bacon), garlic and onion and cook until lightly softened, 12 to 15 minutes.
Add chicken broth and herbs.
Bring to a boil and stir in tortellini.
Simmer, uncovered, until tortellini is cooked, 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and simmer another 5 to 6 minutes.
Add spinach and cook another 5 minutes.
Ladle into bowls; sprinkle on the Parmesan cheese.
Serve with chunks of Italian bread.

title: corn flake biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spread half of butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with half of cereal.
Stir baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto cereal.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Press remaining cereal into dough.
Bake until light brown, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Boil chicken in bouillon for 20 minutes.
Cool and remove skin.
Cook broccoli in broth.
Lay chicken and broccoli in greased pan.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bark cookies
directions: Melt together chocolate bark and peanut butter in 200° oven until soft.
Add other ingredients.
Spoon out on wax paper and cool.
Real good!
Makes approximately 80, depending on size.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Break in pieces.
Layer bottom of dish with chicken.
Layer cooked broccoli, sprinkle with cheese.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over cheese.
Top with crushed, buttered crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with orange salad.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Dip chicken in flour.
Brown in fat.
Remove from bone.
Place in casserole dish with sauteed onions and peppers.
Add seasonings, tomato sauce and water.
Pour over chicken.
Add mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese over casserole 15 minutes before removing from oven.

title: pizza salad
directions: Combine the 2 kinds of lettuce.
Arrange on platter.
Garnish with pepperoni, cheese, onion, tomatoes and olives, making it look like a pizza.

title: whipped banana pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients, except yogurt, in a blender until smooth.
Fold in the yogurt.
Pour into individual sherbet glasses.
Chill well.

title: potato trash
directions: Boil desired number of unpeeled potatoes in water to cover, until tender.
Drain and cut into quarters.
Arrange in 9x13 baking dish.
Add butter, dollops of sour cream, shredded cheese and bacon.

title: sweet layer cookies
directions: Arrange in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in order listed.
Bake at 325° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: julie's pistachio salad
directions: Pour crushed pineapple, including juice, into a bowl.
Stir in pudding mix and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate before serving.
Can be made day before.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured cloth-covered surface.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into 13-inch circle.
Cut circle into 8 wedges.
Place frankfurter one each wedge; roll up, beginning at wide end.
Seal tightly by pinching point into roll.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with mustard or ketchup if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken frickey
directions: Flour your chicken down as if you're going to fry it.
Place in roasting pan.
Put your diced celery, onion and green pepper on top of chicken.
Put a little water on the bottom of pan with butter slices on top of chicken also.
Bake 1 hour.
Good with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: thick white sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour and salt and let bubble up together.
Take off heat, add milk all at once and cook over low to medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: black forest cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake; cool on rack, then refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Take sewing thread and cut each layer in half to make 4 layers.
Open pie filling and mix with almond and vanilla.
Put first layer of cake on plate.
Spread with Cool Whip; top with cherries.
Put second layer on top.
Repeat with remaining filling.
Continue this.
Put fourth layer on top.
Ice with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with shaved chocolate. Refrigerate until serving.

title: cinnamon date batter bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in honey.
Add butter, salt and 2 cups flour.
Beat with mixer on low speed until blended.
Beat 1 minute on high speed.
Stir in remaining flour with wooden spoon.
Cover; let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down by stirring with heavy spoon.
Add cinnamon and dates.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes until loaf sounds hollow when lightly tapped.
Cool on wire rack.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces and brown.
In large saucepan, combine sugar, juice from pineapple, catsup, soy sauce and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with cold water; stir into other hot mixture.
Add pineapple, celery, carrots and chicken.
Bring to a low boil.
If too thick, add orange juice or water.

title: frozen pickles
directions: When sugar is dissolved, add to pickle mixture and stir well. Let stand 10 minutes.
Pack into cartons or jars and put in freezer.
Defrost to serve.

title: mediterranean chicken and rice
directions: Prep - CLEAN:
Wash hands, remove protective ice glaze from frozen chicken by holding under cool water 1 to 2 minutes.
Wash hands AGAIN.

title: strawberry scharm
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and add beaten egg yolks.
Add milk, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Put in 2 greased layer cake pans.
Beat 4 egg whites stiff with 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread over dough and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° to 375° oven.
Put sweetened, mashed or sliced strawberries between layers and cover with whipped cream.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Heat last 5 ingredients to dissolve sugar and salt.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Blend eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in sour cream.
Blend soda, flour and milk, alternating each.
Blend vanilla and pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Salt and
pepper
pork
chops;
dip in flour.
Brown on both sides
in
oil.
Place in Dutch oven or covered casserole dish. Place
slice
of tomato, onion and slice of bell pepper on each chop.
Cover with 1 cup of rice.
Add 2 cups of water. Salt to taste.
Cook
hour in a 350° oven or until water is absorbed by rice.

title: ministers delight
directions: Place filling in bottom of slow cooker. Combine cake mix and butter. Mixture will be crumbly. Sprinkle over filling. Cover and cook on low 2 to 3 hours. Serve in bowls. This is rich and very easy. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cream butter; stir in water and vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in dates and walnuts.
Roll into one inch balls; place 2 1/2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes only.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and celery (whatever amount you like) and saute in margarine.
Mix all other ingredients together and add this to it.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and bake, covered, for 45 minutes in a 425° oven.
Drain; combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered, or until cheese is golden brown.

title: zucchini pie(tastes like apple pie)
directions: *You can substitute 1 teaspoon apple pie spice.

title: caramel pecans
directions: Mix sugar, butter and boiling water.
Let cook without stirring.
When mixture has reached the boiling stage, cook until soft ball stage.
Drop in pecans and continue to cook for 1 minute.
Drop on wax paper.
Separate as much as possible.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to a rolling boil.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Continue beating until smooth.
Drop dough, 1/4 cupful at a time, 3 inches apart onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool away from draft.
Cut off tops.
Pull out any filaments of soft dough. Carefully fill puffs with pudding.
Replace tops.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: hamburger and french bread bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Mix in rest of ingredients, except bread.
Cut bread in half lengthwise; scoop out center of each half.
Fill bread halves with meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage and wild rice
directions: Brown sausage; crumble and drain.
Reserve drippings.
Saute onion and celery in sausage drippings.
Cook rice according to package directions; add sausage, onion and celery, then add mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Turn into a casserole; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is a wonderful brunch dish.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: *Bananas,
grapes, pineapple, marshmallows, berries and nuts.

title: chocolate chips
directions: Melt chips, milk and oleo. Add flour and salt. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 7 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough onto a pizza pan or two 9-inch rounds for crust.
Bake and cool as package directs.
Whip together the cream cheese, sour cream and powdered sugar; spread on cool crust. Arrange strawberries (halved) on top of cream mixture.
Stir glaze mix with strawberry gelatin.
Cool and pour over berries.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Refrigerate until gelatin glaze sets.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook broccoli.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, grated cheese and seasonings.
In 3-quart casserole dish, layer broccoli, Parmesan cheese, chicken, Parmesan cheese, sauce, Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Dot with butter. Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: "cheaters" grape juice
directions: Stem and wash grapes.
You need two cups of grapes per quart jar and one-half cup or less of sugar per jar.
Fill with boiling water.
Make sure jars, lids and rings are hot.

title: mini cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of a cupcake paper.
Fill each with mixture, 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool and top with cherry pie filling.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt butter in microwave or skillet.
Add remaining seasonings.
Stir in pecans, coating with mixture.
Bake in single layer on a cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes until brown. Stir occasionally while baking at 300°.

title: zero-calorie salad dressing
directions: Shake well; pour over salad.
Can be stored in refrigerator several weeks.
Yield: 1/2 cup.

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and molasses. Sift in dry ingredients; blend well.
Form teaspoonfuls of dough in balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned and cracked. Bake at 350°.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together.
Pour over pickle mixture and let set for 2 or 3 hours.
Package and freeze.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Chop dates; mix with hot water and set aside.
Mix together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix in dates and 1/2 package chips.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle other 1/2 package chips and chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: lemon bread
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add water and oil.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until moistened, then beat for 2 minutes at medium speed or 400 strokes by hand.
Spread batter evenly into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and yellow cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts or green parsley.
Serve with fancy crackers.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place all ingredients in layers in a large bowl (except mayonnaise and sugar which is put on top).
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Stir before serving.
Delicious!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream margarine, peanut butter, sugars, eggs, and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Press five peanut halves atop each, or crisscross with fork.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, flour and water together in saucepan; boil until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add cooled dressing.
Use more egg to garnish, if you wish.
You can also use carrots, diced small, to give color.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanuts.
Spread mixture into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.

title: orange spice tea
directions: Mix ingredients together in jar with a tight fitting lid.
Use as instant beverage, hot or cold.
One to 2 tablespoons per 8 ounce glass or to taste.

title: frito plate
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Place Fritos on plates.
Add sauce to cover.
Sprinkle with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and black or green olives.
Top with sour cream.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 3-quart rectangular casserole dish, spread layer of lettuce.
Cover lettuce with layer of celery.
Cover celery with a layer of onion.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and salt and spread over onion layer.
Crumble crisp bacon over mayonnaise layer.
Sprinkle layer of uncooked chopped broccoli over bacon.
Cover broccoli with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate.
Prepare 12 to 24 hours before serving.
Keeps 2 to 3 days.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Simmer hamburger in small amount of fat until cooked, not brown.
Add and simmer slowly chili powder, minced onions, garlic and salt.
Add and simmer for 30 minutes hot catsup, kidney beans and jalapeno bean dip.
Place in chafing dish.
Sprinkle around edge, shredded sharp Cheddar cheese and finely minced onions.

title: sauerkraut and wieners
directions: Cut wieners up into small chunks and put into boiler of water. Boil for about 15 minutes.
Pour off water.
Add can of sauerkraut, tomato sauce and small amount of water.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail 4 minute icing
directions: Put bottom of double boiler on flame; fill with water so top will fit 1-inch in water.
Boil water.
Take from flame; put on flat surface to beat.
Place all ingredients in top of boiler.
Set in bottom pan of hot water and beat 4 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese until smooth. Set aside 1 cup pecans. Combine all ingredients and form into ball. Roll ball in other cup of pecans.

title: stuffed macaroni shells
directions: Follow cooking directions on shell package.
Stuff shells with meat mixture.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage rounds
directions: Brown ground chuck and sausage together.
Drain.
In a large saucepan mix cheese, mushrooms and oregano until cheese melts and coats all ingredients.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of mixture on rye rounds and freeze.
At anytime, take from freezer and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes about 40 rounds.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook beef, onions, and pepper together in skillet until done. Add the other ingredients except spaghetti.
Cook spaghetti, separate until done.
Add 1 tsp salt, then add to the other ingredients.
Ready to serve!

title: holly's beans
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Saute ground beef with bacon; add onion and saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour into 13 x 9 baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for approximately 1 hour or 3 hours on low in crock-pot.
May use 1/2 ground turkey and 1/2 ground beef.

title: *fried apples
directions: Melt butter.
Add apples and sprinkle with flour and sugar that have been mixed together.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until apples are tender.
These are delicious with sausage.
Red hots, added with the sugar, add zing.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar and beat.
Add oil and vanilla and beat.
In a separate bowl, mix first 5 ingredients.
Gradually add to egg mixture using spoon.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 75 minutes.

title: easy yorkshire dinner
directions: Sprinkle ground beef and onion with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes at 400°; drain and remove.
Beat egg, milk and mayonnaise together.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Pour over ground beef.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit filled crumb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pie filling.
Spread 3/4 dough on a cookie sheet.
Cover dough with choice of canned pie filling (2 cans).
Grate remaining 1/4 dough over the fruit.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Sift powdered sugar over the top when cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and honey until well mixed.
Stir in peanut butter, mix well.
Gently fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust.
Heat chocolate chips and shortening over low heat until melted.
Drizzle chocolate over pie.
Chill for at least 4 hours.
Serve chilled.

title: tomato salad
directions: Combine everything (except tomatoes) in a jar and shake well. Pour over tomatoes.
Refrigerate about 4 hours.

title: biscuits with yeast(servings:  8)
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix in shortening with fork.
Dissolve yeast in milk and proceed as you would for any other biscuits.
Mix well and roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Grease pan and grease biscuits with melted fat.
Set aside until ready to bake (15 or 20 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: ellie's cookies(molasses)
directions: Mix lard, brown sugar, molasses and milk.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, mix all other ingredients; combine.
Drop tablespoon size balls onto greased cookie sheet.
Press to flatten.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix well.
Add a little more water if needed to make it easily workable.	Flour
board to work on.
Makes 5 crusts (2 double crust
pies
and 1 single bottom layer).
This makes a great crust and is
especially	dependable crust for a chicken pie.

title: squash casserole
directions: In frying pan, combine shortening, squash, onions, salt and pepper.
Cook until done.
Drain well.
Pour in casserole dish. Cool about 15 minutes.
Beat eggs, then stir into squash and onions.
Put cheese on top of squash.
Sprinkle crushed saltines over cheese.
Preheat oven at 350° and bake for 20 minutes.
Based on 8 servings.
Per serving:
248 calories; 20g fat; 421mg sodium; 69mg cholesterol.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Cover chicken with flour, coat skillet with Pam.
Melt butter, add floured chicken breasts.
Cook over medium heat until brown on both sides (5 to 7 minutes).
Remove chicken; stir in teriyaki sauce, lemon juice, garlic and sugar.
Put chicken back in pan and simmer 3 minutes on each side.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for egg whites. Beat whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Place in greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown and crispy.
Excellent served with buttered noodles and a green vegetable.
Very colorful plate.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice and turn into large bowl.
Remove artichoke hearts, cut into halves or thirds.
Reserve.
To marinade in jar, add the oil, vinegar and mustard.
Cover jar and shake to blend.
With a fork, stir into hot rice.
Cool to room temperature.
To rice mixture, add artichoke, tuna, pepper and scallions and toss well. Serve at room temperature or chill.

title: butterscotch pie("favorite family pie")
directions: Combine in double boiler the first 5 ingredients.
Cook for 15 minutes, until thickened.
Add beaten egg yolks (blend some mixture into the eggs first, then pour all of it into the rest of the mixture).
Cook 3 more minutes.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla; mix well.
Cool.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Makes 1 pie.
Top with meringue.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in milk.
Add sugar and corn syrup; cook slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook gently to soft ball stage (234°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool at room temperature to lukewarm (110°) without stirring.
Add vanilla.
Beat vigorously until fudge becomes very thick and loses its gloss.
Quickly spread in greased pan.
When firm, cut in squares.
One cup broken nuts may be added, or the fudge may be kneaded when hard, formed into rolls and sliced.
If desired, 1/3 cup cocoa may be substituted for the unsweetened chocolate (increase butter to 3 teaspoons).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done; drain.
Combine all other ingredients; stir in broccoli.
Put into Pam sprayed 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers; dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together. Place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with Ry-Krisps or crackers.

title: raspberry bavarian jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and salt with boiling water. Add raspberries. Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip. Place in Jell-O mold until firm.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Melt chocolate.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: quick vegetable dish
directions: Place all ingredients in a covered casserole dish.
Cook for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: tomato-okra side dish
directions: Pour tomatoes into kettle; put sliced okra pods in tomatoes and add corn.
Season to taste with salt and sugar.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Lower heat and cook until vegetables are done.
Serve in a small bowl with meal.
Serves 10.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until barely done.
Drain. Cook onion gently in 1/3 cup oleo until slightly browned. Stir in flour, salt and mustard. Stir in milk until milk is smooth. Add pepper, celery, salt and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted.
Place carrots in a casserole dish. Pour sauce over the carrots. Top with bread cubes which have been sauteed in oleo. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: camp cookies
directions: Bake for 8-10 minutes (just until firm) at 350 degrees.

title: sausage cornbread dressing
directions: In large frying pan, lightly brown sausage.
Add celery and onion and cook about 10 minutes.
Mix crumbs, sage and chicken broth.
Add sausage, onion and celery.
Mix well.
Bake in buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish at 350° until browned (depending on oven, can be between 30 and 45 minutes).

title: celebration potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until done, 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain, cool, then refrigerate until called for.
Chop next 5 ingredients and combine with mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, mustard and salt in a bowl and mix well.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes, peeled if preferred.
Add potatoes to mixture and stir gently until mixed well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yiayia's greek chicken breasts with potatoes
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Season with salt, pepper and oregano. Spray baking pan lightly with cooking spray.
Place seasoned chicken into baking pan, meaty side down.
Dot with butter. Squeeze lemon juice over chicken.
Add a small amount of water to pan.
Cook for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Turn chicken over.
Place potatoes around chicken.
Turn potatoes to coat with drippings. Add a little more salt and pepper to the potatoes if you like. Bake an additional 1/2 hour or until chicken is done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add warm water and knead until dough is soft, not sticky.
Stretch and pat dough until thin.
Tear off one piece at a time; poke a hole in the center. Drop into skillet of hot cooking oil.
Brown on both sides.
Serve hot.
Very good with honey
or dusted with powdered sugar.
Makes delicious hamburger buns sliced into two taco shells.

title: broccoli and cheese dip(servings:  10)
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box and drain completely.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine cheese and mushroom soup and heat, stirring, until melted.
Add onion, broccoli and red pepper.
Serve with Melba rounds.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in shortening, sugar and egg and beat in flour.
Store in refrigerator.
Take out and use amount desired.
Will keep for 1 week in refrigerator.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pan; add graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Pat out in pan and bake at 250° for about 15 minutes. Cool graham cracker crumbs.
Whip Dream Whip, milk, vanilla and cream cheese.
Spread over graham crackers.
Dribble pie filling on top of this.
Store in refrigerator.

title: confetti dip
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together until smooth. Fold in pickles, pimiento and egg. Cover and chill to blend flavors. Serve as a dip for potato chips, pretzels or raw vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray a large cookie sheet with Pam cooking spray.
Spread entire cookie dough roll out onto the cookie sheet.
Bake as directed, until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: health bran squares
directions: Combine bran, oats, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add chopped nuts, dates and lemon rind.
Stir in beaten eggs, honey and yogurt, mixing well.
Blend in oil.
Pour in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 24 bars to be fed to hungry children.
We are what we eat.

title: cornish hens & rice pilaf
directions: Clean and prepare the quantity of Cornish Hens that are appropriate for the people being served.
Place in a 350 - 375 oven for 1 hour.
I put a bit of margarine on the outside of the hen and sometimes sprinkle it with Garlic Salt.
In a skillet, place 1/4 c. of Margarine, cook Onion until golden.
Put into a 2 quart casserole dish with a cover and set aside.
In same skillet, heat remaining margarine, brown the Rice so that it is fluffy and golden brown.
Add to the casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake for 350 - 375 for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients. Season with salt and pepper if desired.
Place in 3-quart buttered casserole (flat pan).
Refrigerate and bake (next day if desired). Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Top should be lightly browned. (Optional:
Put grated cheese on top last 10 minutes.)
Can freeze unbaked and use when needed.

title: stuffed mushroom appetizer
directions: Melt butter in a pan on stove and slightly brown mushroom tops after you've twisted and pulled out stems of whole mushrooms. Brown both sides.
Cube the cheeses and drop one into browned mushroom "cup".
Sprinkle with thyme and a dash of sage.
Heat in 350° preheated oven until cheese melts, about 5 minutes, on a cookie sheet.

title: best chocolate rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum for quality.
Now go ahead and select a large mixing bowl.
Check the rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure of this, pour one cup of rum into a glass and drink it.
Repeat.
With electric mixer, beat one cup buerrer in the large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of thugar and beat again. Drink another cup of rum to ensure quality.
Add 2 arge leggs, 2 cups fried druit and beat until high.
If the druit gets stuck in the beaters, pry loose with a drewscriver.
Sample the rum again. Sift 1/2 pint of lemon juice.
Sample the rum again.
Sift 3 cups of pepper or salt (it doesn't matter).
Fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add 1 babblespoon of brown thugar or whatever color you find.
Wix mel.
Grease oven and turn cake pan to 350 gredees. Now pour the whole mess into the boven and cake.
Check rum again and bo to ged.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put berries in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, water and lemon juice.
In a large bowl, mix remaining ingredients until crumbly and pour evenly over berries.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes, until top is golden brown.

title: brownie pudding cake
directions: Prepare batter:
Stir together flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add milk, oil and vanilla. Stir until smooth.
Mix in walnuts.
Spread evenly in 8-inch square glass dish.

title: night owl snack
directions: Spread peanut butter on cracker.
Cut 3 slices of banana.
Use 2 slices for eyes, dip 2 raisins in peanut butter and add to center of banana.
Take the other slice of banana and cut in half. Use 1/2 turned sideways for nose.
Add crumbled cereal for eyebrows.

title: pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans in pie shell.
In large bowl, beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over pecans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 minutes or until tested done.
Cool on rack.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add pecans and apples.
Bake in sheet cake pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jack frost warmer
directions: Mix all ingredients. Heat.
Serve hot. Remove any cloves from cups.
Very good.

title: homemade shake and bake
directions: Mix
together
well.
Cut
in
shortening
with
pastry blender
until
resembles	fine
crumbs.
Store
in
airtight container.	Makes 6 cups of mix.
Use 1 cup mix per chicken or 6 to	8 pork chops.
Coat meat with mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Spray pan with non-stick cooking spray before baking.

title: steam ahead asparagus
directions: Cut the stalks of the asparagus about 2 to 3-inches from the bottom. Peel the stalks up to 1/2-inch from the tip with a sharp vegetable peeler. Asparagus can be left in spears or cut into pieces as desired. In a 10 to 12-inch saut pan, bring 1/2-inch water and salt to a boil. Add the asparagus to the pan and cover it. Bring the water back to a boil and simmer for 2 minutes. The asparagus should be bright green and somewhat limp. Drain the water off and immediately run cold water into the pan. This will stop the cooking process and retain the color of the asparagus. When the asparagus is cold, drain it and set aside until you are ready to reheat it.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix well and press into 9-inch pie plate.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix your sugar and cream upon low heat until the sugar dissolves.
Boil on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Take off burner and add butter and marshmallow cream.
Mix it up and pour it in a buttered pan.
Let cool.

title: flying taco salad dip
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread refried beans on bottom of pan; spread taco sauce over beans.
Add cheese and one thin layer of lettuce, then spread lots of chopped tomatoes.
Last, spread onions or green peppers on top.
Use tortilla chips, potato chips or Doritos.
Serve cold or put in 350° oven about 15 minutes.
This is very good.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix lemon juice, onions, mustard, garlic powder and horseradish sauce.
Fold in crabmeat; place on serving dish.
Chill several hours.
Top with shrimp sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: cubed steak casserole
directions: Layer steak on bottom of casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Layer onions, carrots and then potatoes.
Heat soup, water and margarine and pour over other ingredients.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: chicken pepper pasta
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, melt butter until sizzling.
Stir in onion, peppers and garlic.
Cook over medium-high heat until peppers are crisply tender (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove vegetables with slotted spoon; set aside, reserving juices in pan.
Add chicken, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until chicken is lightly browned and fork-tender (7 to 9 minutes).

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: parmesan noodles
directions: In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, 2 tablespoons butter, parsley, basil and lemon-pepper.
Stir in water; keep warm.
In a saucepan, saut garlic in remaining butter until lightly browned. Place noodles in a serving bowl; top with garlic mixture. Sprinkle with half of the Parmesan cheese; toss lightly.
Spoon cream sauce over noodles and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Garnish with parsley if desired.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Beat egg.
Add meat.
Take 2 slices bread and cut the crust off.
Tear the bread in little pieces and add to 1/2 cup milk just as it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and beat the bread with a fork until it is smooth; let cool.
Add the following to the ground meat:
salt, onion, garlic and parsley.
Now add the cooled bread and milk mixture.
Mix with hands until well blended.
Add a little oil.
Make meatballs and fry until brown.
Add to spaghetti sauce.

title: coco-nut caramel chews(microwave)
directions: Line a 8 by 8-inch square microwave safe dish with plastic wrap allowing the wrap to come over the sides.
Spray the prepared dish with cooking spray.
Spray a medium size, microwave safe bowl with cooking spray.
To the prepared bowl, add the caramel candies, peanuts, white chocolate and 1/2 cup of the coconut.
Give it a stir to combine.
Set the microwave for 1 minute 30 seconds on high.
Place the bowl in the microwave and cook 1 minute.
Stop the microwave, stir the mixture, return to microwave to cook 30 seconds longer.
Remove the mixture and stir.
Scrape it into the prepared square pan.
Flatten the mixture with a rubber spatula evenly. Cover the top of the candy with remaining coconut, using the rubber spatula to press it in slightly.

If the mixture is too firm on top for the coconut to stick, place the mixture back in the microwave for 10 seconds, then resume pressing the coconut into the candy. Allow the candies to cool completely.
Remove the entire block, using the plastic wrap to help you pull it out.
Using a sharp knife, cut candy into small, 1-inch squares.

title: pasta and vegetable toss
directions: In large skillet cook onion, garlic and Italian seasoning in oil until tender.
Add water, bouillon and vegetables.
Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes until vegetables are tender crisp.
Toss with hot fettucini.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate.
Makes 4 servings

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells in boiling salt water according to package directions until tender but still firm. Drain.

title: plum kuchen(or whatever fruit is in season.)
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mixture will be doughy.
Slice fruit on top of mixture; press slightly down.
Bake in a 9-inch cake pan at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook until thick, then add 1/2 cup of sweet cream.
Cool and mix in potatoes, celery and onion for a salad.

title: peach or fig cobbler
directions: Put fruit in 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Add lemon juice or extract; mix well.
Mix sugar and flour.
Beat egg slightly and add to sugar-flour mixture to make crumbles.

title: sweet potato angel biscuits
directions: Wash sweet potatoes; bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done. Let potatoes cool; peel and mash.
Set aside 3 cups and keep warm. Combine yeast and warm water in a 2-cup liquid measuring cup. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and oleo or butter.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to cooled milk mixture:
eggs and 2 cups flour.
Mix well and add 3 1/4 cups flour or more/less as needed to make soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover with towel and let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Punch down; divide into thirds and turn on lightly floured board.
Roll into a large circle and spread with melted oleo or butter.
Cut into pie size pieces and roll up, beginning at wide end, sealing points firmly.
Place on greased baking sheets with points underneath, about 2-inches apart.
Curve to form crescents.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Bake about 12 minutes in 350° to 400° oven.
After taking out of oven, brush a little butter on top.
(I use a paper towel dipped in soft butter.)

title: fluffy lemon fruit pie
directions: Place strawberries in bottom of crust. Beat cream cheese in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gradually beat in milk until well blended. Add pudding mix and beat until smooth. Gently stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping. Spread over fruit. Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Garnish with additional fruit if desired.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Add frozen concentrates then add Brandy. Mix well and freeze.
Serve with 7-up or sprite.

title: filled christmas cookies
directions: Work all ingredients as for pie crust.
Make dough into small balls, the size of a walnut or smaller.
Place in bowl with waxed paper between layers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in a small amount of butter in saucepan.
Add cabbage and soups.
Mix well.
Spoon into buttered baking dish. Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix and press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rare roast beef
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Put into pan, fat side up. Do not cover or add water.
Have oven preheated to 375°.
Cook meat for 1 hour. Turn off heat.
Do not open oven door at anytime. Thirty or 40 minutes before serving, turn oven to 375° again and cook meat for 30 minutes.
Put the roast in oven anytime between 10:00 a.m. and 3:00 p.m. for evening meal.
Very good to slice leftovers if any left for sandwich.
Tape oven door if necessary to keep from opening.

title: hungarian noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Combine noodles with remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased baking dish in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: middle eastern salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and chill.
Makes 1 to 4 servings.
One cup equals 25 calories and 0 fat.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Put into slow cooker.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until ready to use.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In large bowl pour milk over sugar, salt and butter.
In another small bowl dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
When milk mix is same temperature as yeast mix, put together in large bowl and add 1/2 of flour.
Beat by hand or by electric mixer about 5 minutes or less by electric mixer.
Add rest of flour, turn out on floured board and knead until dough is glossy and elastic.
Place in buttered bowl and cover with dish towel.
When doubled in size punch down and roll into 3 loaves.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 300° or 350° for 1 hour or 45 minutes depending on pans.
Turn out on rack and butter crust.

title: tropical banana cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bananas, in a bowl.
Beat 3 minutes.
Fold in bananas.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.
Frost with spicy cream cheese frosting.
Garnish top with banana slices.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans in a 375° oven or 350° if using glass loaf pans.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and peppers.
Drain.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, corn and cooked macaroni. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cheese drip
directions: Roll chicken in eggs and then bread crumbs.
Fry chicken in olive oil for 20 minutes.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken, top with cheese.
Cover and cook for additional 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Grease baking pan or casserole dish.
Mix ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Cook in 350° oven until bubbling in center.

title: recipe for revival
directions: If my people, which are called by my name, shall humble themselves and pray, and seek my face, and turn from their wicked ways; then will I hear from heaven, and will forgive their sin, and will heal their land.

title: quick breakfast bake
directions: Tear the bread and place the pieces in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown and drain well the pork sausage. Spoon evenly over bread pieces. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, nectar, sugar and oil.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing after each addition.
Bake in greased and floured tube or bundt pun at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender-crisp and drain.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish (buttered). Combine eggs, cheese, mayonnaise and soup.
Pour over hot broccoli. Toss croutons with melted butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: harvest moon cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Bake in greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread with frosting when cool.

title: marinated veggies and rice
directions: For marinade, combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl. Add veggies to marinade and toss to coat.
