Cover and chill; add rice and toss lightly to combine.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or with mixer.
Pour into 10 x 10-inch casserole.
Add topping.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Fill cones halfway.
Stand on a rimmed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: raspberry rhubarb salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add the rhubarb sauce. Stir in the pared and chopped apples. Refrigerate.

title: chocoholic's cookie
directions: Sift oatmeal to a fine powder and set aside.
Cream together margarine, sugar and brown sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and oatmeal.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and pecans.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Gently mix first 4 ingredients.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Place sugar, vinegar, oil and salt in a 2-quart pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables while hot.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: pineapple apricot jello salad
directions: Then stir in cream cheese and let cool. Fold in 1 cup Dream Whip and spread over Jell-O mixture.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix everything together except cheese and chips.
Put in an 11 x 7 or 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Serve with chips.
Can be made ahead.
Refrigerate, then bake 1/2 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Stir butter or margarine into hot spaghetti.
Stir in grated cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust," in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread Ricotta cheese over bottom of spaghetti crust.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together, then mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour into 2 pie shells (unbaked).
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Cream margarine, 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour. Spread dough in bottom of a 9-inch pan.
Combine cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add egg.
Mix and pour into pan.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar, apples and cinnamon, and put over cheese layer.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 400° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: southern barbecue
directions: Slowly cook the roast with the vinegar, pepper and enough water to cover roast in crock-pot all day.
When cooked, remove roast and let cool.
Save 1 cup of juice from the crock-pot and discard the rest.
With fork, separate the meat.
Return the meat to crock-pot.
Add 1 cup of juices and barbecue sauce.
Heat and serve.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread and crumble. Add remaining ingredients. Toss and serve. Best chilled.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt Velveeta in microwave.
Combine all ingredients and return to microwave until bubbly.
Serve with nachos.

title: mother's day muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients except buttermilk and butter or margarine in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add butter or margarine and buttermilk.
Mix lightly until mixture is just moistened.
Pour batter in greased muffin tin 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rice dressing
directions: Put all ingredients except rice in a large heavy pot. Bring almost to boiling, then add rice; stir well. Seal top of pot with foil and fit lid on tightly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. After 1 hour, if rice isn't done, take foil off and bake until done.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add teaspoon sugar and egg. Stir in 3 cups flour.
Add melted shortening.
Stir in remainder of flour.

title: heavenly squares
directions: Mix flour and melted butter for crust.
Bake in 8 x 10-inch pan at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger meat and pork sausage together; add salt and pepper.
Mix rest of ingredients with meat and 1/2 can of sauce. Form into a loaf.
Put in loaf pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Put the other 1/2 can of sauce over meat loaf 15 minutes before it is done.
Bake at 350°.

title: marla's lemon bars
directions: Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated black olives
directions: Mix.
Pour over 1 can drained black olives.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Simmer celery, onion, salt, pepper and turkey pieces in water, covered, for about an hour.
Strain, measure and add water to make 4 cups.
Chop giblets and add to stock.
After removing turkey from oven, pour off fat, leaving brown drippings in pan.
Put about 1/2 cup of fat back into pan.
Blend in flour and cook, stirring all the while, until mixture bubbles.
Stir in stock and giblets and continue cooking, while stirring, until gravy thickens; boil a minute or two.
Makes 3 to 4 cups.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and bake.
Place 1 cake layer in the bottom of the punch bowl.
Prepare instant pudding.
Use half on the first layer.
Slice 1 to 1 1/2 bananas over the instant pudding.
Pour 1/2 can of the pineapple over the bananas and pour one carton of the strawberries over the pineapple.
Then top with one carton of Cool Whip.
Repeat directions with second cake layer.
After both cakes are in the punch bowl, sprinkle pecan halves on the top.
Put in the refrigerator and let chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: hot cole slaw
directions: Cook cabbage.
Add cream or milk, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Can cook with red pepper pod for spicing.

title: pearl salad
directions: Put pineapple in pot and bring to a boil.
Put in 2 tablespoons sugar.
Take off heat.
Pour on Jell-O and dissolve. Put in buttermilk.
Set pot in refrigerator and cool.
Stir in Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour in pan and refrigerate.

title: steak with hearty mustard marinade
directions: Combine mustard, soy sauce, wine, sugar, oil, garlic and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Place steak in shallow dish or plastic bag; add marinade.
Cover and refrigerate 5 hours.
Remove meat from marinade.
Place on grill about 5 inches from source of heat. Brush with marinade.
Grill 15 minutes.
Turn meat and brush with marinade.
Grill 10 minutes longer or until desired doneness. Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until half done.
Rinse in ice water.
Layer carrots, peppers and onions alternately.
Place remaining ingredients in saucepan and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: kraut burgers
directions: In large deep skillet, brown hamburger and onion.
Then cover meat with water (about 4 cups).
Shred cabbage and place in skillet.
Mash down so it is covered with the water.
Cover and simmer on a medium heat until cabbage is just tender.
Mix up meat with the cabbage, then pour into a colander in sink and let drain thoroughly.

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add raspberries and pineapple. Chill until partially thickened.
Add bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread cream on top.
Spread rest of gelatin over all.
Chill.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, water, salt and lime overnight. Rinse, then place in a large pot. Add vinegar, sugar and spices. Cook until thick, about 3 hours. Put into hot, sterile jars and seal.

title: walking taco dip or 7 layer
directions: First, you will need a large tray, about the size of a cookie sheet.
Spread bean dip evenly over the bottom of the tray with a spatula.
Sprinkle Ortega chiles over the beans.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in separate bowl, then spread over chilies.
You may use either store bought avocado dip or homemade. Spread it over the cream mixture.
Remember, you want to keep this in layers, like a pizza.
You should have four layers by now. Cover those layers with a thick layer of Cheddar cheese, covering all the mixture.
Sprinkle onions, olives and tomatoes over the cheese and your dip is complete.
Feeds 20 to 30 people.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Chop and cook broccoli until barely tender.
Drain well.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Flake chicken or ham with fork. Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Put gelatin in water.
Separate eggs.
Put whites in mixing bowl.
Put yolks in top of double boiler, add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Cook over boiling water, beating constantly until thick.
Add gelatin.
Let cool.
Add rest of sugar.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: holiday spiced tea
directions: Boil 4 cups water with sugar, cloves, &

cinnamon for 10 minutes. Remove from heat, add tea bags. Let steep until cool. Strain, add juice and additional 12 cups of water. Reheat when ready to serve. Makes 5 quarts. Great for the holidays, plus it smells great.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet; remove from pan.
In skillet, saute onion and celery until slightly tender.
Add soup and milk. In large casserole, layer potatoes, cabbage, flour (sprinkled) and some of soup mixture.
Repeat process until all ingredients are used.
Place pork chops on top of casserole.
Bake, covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until potatoes are done.

title: skillet supper
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and green bell pepper in a large skillet. Cut sausage diagonally into 1-inch chunks and combine with vegetables.
Add water and seasonings. Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: yummy potato bake
directions: Defrost potatoes thoroughly.
Fold together all ingredients. Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: burgundy fruitcake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add 1 cup flour, mixing well.
Combine remaining 1 cup flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Add eggs; beat with an electric mixer until well blended.
Add batter to fruit mixture, stirring well.
Spoon batter into a greased and brown paper lined 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake completely in pan.
Remove from pan and remove brown paper.
Wrap cake in cheesecloth soaked in 1/2 cup wine; store in an airtight container at least 1 week before serving.

title: marrow bone butter
directions: Crack bones and roast in 350° oven for 1 hour or when marrow feels soft.
Scoop out marrow and season with salt and pepper. Serve on Indian bread or tortillas.

title: aja's cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll ball in crushed pecans.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix sugar, margarine and eggs. Add flour, vanilla and nutmeg; mix well. Then add buttermilk. Pour into 9-inch deep unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: squash souffle
directions: Slice, cook and drain squash.
Add mayonnaise to beaten eggs. Add squash, onion and crackers (rolled fine).
Add salt, then blend well.
Pour into buttered dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: daniel's treat
directions: Blend well with spoon or hands.
Mold into ball shape, using about 1 tablespoonful of mix.
Press firmly together and roll in loose coconut.
A healthy treat for everyone.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with beater until fluffy. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: giant pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and add sugar.
Add flour and knead 6 minutes.
Let dough rise, covered, in a greased bowl until double in size.
Divide dough into 12 pieces and roll into long sticks.
Blend egg yolk and water.
Brush onto pretzels. Place pretzels on cookie sheet.
You can twist the pretzels or shape them into letters.
Sprinkle with coarse salt or sesame seed.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes 12 giant pretzels.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Mix drained pineapple, bananas, nuts and Cool Whip with cranberry sauce and sugar.
Freeze.
Take out 30 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients together to make meat sauce.
Mix remaining ingredients together except for the Mozzarella cheese to make the cheese mixture.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put thin layer of tomato sauce mixture in bottom of pan.
Next, layer uncooked lasagna noodles, next 1/2 of cottage cheese mixture and then 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layering, saving some tomato mixture for top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break
up the bread into pieces and line pan. Next add sausage.

title: fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in 6-quart saucepan and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter, margarine and nuts.
Beat until thick.
Spread on buttered dish and let cool.
(Can add 1 cup marshmallow if you like or 1/3 jar Marshmallow Creme.)

title: mae's pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy, about two minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix next four ingredients.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add 1/4 of flour mixture to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Add 1/3 cup of milk.
Keep adding flour and milk alternately, ending with flour. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until no longer doughy in the middle.
Use a tube mold.

title: squash balls
directions: Beat egg; add milk, onions and squash. Mix well. Add flour and cornmeal together and stir into squash mixture. Spoon squash mixture into a little ball and drop into hot grease. Cook until brown.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans and pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Yields 2 pies.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Beat eggs and stir in buttermilk, brown sugar and shortening. Add remaining ingredients; stir until flour is dampened.
Batter will not be smooth.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 5 minutes.
Drain and pat dry.
Slice.
In a pan large enough to hold the potatoes in one layer, add enough olive oil to coat the bottom generously.
Add potatoes and garlic and toss to coat.
Add rosemary, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, turning occasionally, until golden brown.

title: potato stick salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together except potato sticks.
Just before serving, add potato sticks.

title: mistake
directions: Combine meat, onion, salt and pepper in skillet; cook, stirring, until browned and meat is broken up.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes until heated.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: *Well drain these vegetables.

title: carol's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone; cut into small pieces or strips. Place chicken in bottom of dish (9 x 13-inch).
Combine soup, sour cream and grated cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine in pan and add Ritz.
Stir well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Fry over high heat in 4 tablespoons oil for 5 minutes.
Add bamboo shoots, pea pods, celery, cabbage, water chestnuts, broth and soy.
Cover pan and steam for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Mix cornstarch with cold water.
Add to Moo Goo Gai Pan to thicken.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: In large pot, bring cooked chicken to boil in broth.
Let simmer (slow boil).
Mix together baking mix and 2/3 cup milk. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto boiling chicken mixture.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve hot.
Great with potato salad and baked beans.

title: ham and cheese souffle
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Lay 8 slices of bread on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cheese, ham and vegetables, if desired, over bread.
Put 8 more slices on top.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over bread slices in pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: grandma's corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together well, then add the milk and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add cornbread mix.
Add grated cheese. Bake in well-greased 2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
Top will be golden brown.

title: italian chicken tenders
directions: Place raw chicken tenders in casserole dish.
Cover with Italian dressing.
Cover dish with Saran Wrap.
Place in refrigerator for 4 to 5 hours for marinating.
Take out 30 minutes before ready to fry.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1 coffee measure per mug.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare fresh broccoli and cook until tender.
Melt Cheez Whiz and stir in 3/4 stick of margarine. Crush the package of Ritz crackers.
When broccoli is tender, pour broccoli into pie plate.
Pour Cheez Whiz and margarine mixture over the cooked broccoli.
Spread crushed crackers over the top and pour remaining margarine on top of crackers.
Place in oven and bake until golden brown.

title: frontier stew
directions: Brown ground beef in bacon drippings, separating meat with a fork as it cooks.
Add onions, green pepper, garlic and celery; cook until vegetables are soft.
Add chili powder, sugar, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add tomatoes with their liquid, breaking them up with a knife or the back of a spoon.
Add corn, beans, potatoes and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring well.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir occasionally during cooking.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme together; fold in Cool Whip.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Salt ribs and place in shallow roasting pan, meaty side up. Roast at 450° for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, chili, Tabasco sauce and water. Bring to a boil and cook for about 3 minutes.
Drain off excess from meat.
Top each piece with lemon and onion slices.
Pour sauce over ribs and return to oven.
Cook at 350° until ribs are well done, about 1 hour.
Baste with sauce about every 15 minutes. Thin sauce with water if it gets too thick.

title: nineties breakfast dish
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine and brown mushrooms and onions for 6 to 8 minutes until tender.
Stir in pepper; remove mixture from pan and set aside.
In same pan, simmer sausage in 1/2 cup water, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain water.
Slice sausage in 1/4-inch slices and brown slightly.
Drain fat and put sausage on paper towels.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish with nonstick vegetable spray.
Layer half the bread, the mushroom mixture, sausage and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with the cheese.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray or grease and flour.
Mix all cake ingredients until well blended.
Pour cake mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pike's peak peach cobbler
directions: Arrange peaches in well-buttered 8-inch square pan or deep casserole; sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup Holly granulated sugar, lemon juice, lemon peel and almond extract.
Heat peaches in 375° oven while preparing dough.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat well or cream well.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoons 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: green pea salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, onion and peas in glass casserole or large salad bowl.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise together and spread over top.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites with sugar until stiff. Do not underbeat.
Add salt, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased foil-covered cookie sheet.
Put in oven and turn off heat immediately.
Leave overnight (or minimum of 6 hours) without opening oven door.
Yields 36 cookies.

title: fried eggplant or zucchini
directions: In large bowl, combine bread crumbs and spices.
In another bowl, beat eggs and milk.
Slice eggplant or zucchini about 1/8 inch thick.
Dip in egg mixture; dredge through bread crumbs.

title: linguini salad with chicken and dill
directions: Cook linguini according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Cube cooked chicken.
Toss chicken, peas and cooked linguini with rest of ingredients.
Serve immediately, or chill to serve later.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients.
Combine in
a saucepan until melted the margarine, water and cocoa. Combine both mixtures.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix slow at first.
Mix well. Pour into an 11 x 16-inch greased cookie sheet with 1/2-inch rim.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cake pulls from sides. Ice.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into 9-inch deep dish graham cracker pie shell.
No setting necessary. Top with sliced strawberries or your favorite fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Make well in center of dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans; mix well.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Pour into 6 greased 6 x 3 x 2-inch foil pans or 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes for foil pans or 1 hour for large pans.
Remove from oven and let cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans.
Remove from pans and finish cooling on wire rack.

title: pretzel sparklers
directions: A recipe that is not shared with others

title: quick sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks; cream in the sugar.
Add exactly 3 tablespoons of cold water.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and baking powder.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Bake about 1 hour at 325° or until firm to the touch and a delicate brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place the chicken in a baking dish.
Mix together the soups and milk, and pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over the chicken and soup mixture.
Mix the chicken broth and margarine and pour over the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cornbread for dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon grease.
Stir well.
Heat grease in a large iron skillet or a 9 x 13-inch heavy pan until very hot.
Pour in mixture.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until well browned.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly and form shape needed before refrigerating. It's best to keep in refrigerator at least a day before using.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with lettuce, cauliflower, crumbled bacon and diced onion.
Mix remaining ingredients for dressing.
Put on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit
and yogurt; mix well.
Chill thoroughly. Serve on lettuce if desired.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in freezer.
Remove 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses together.
Mix Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and onion.
Mix both together.
Make into a ball and refrigerate until hard.
Remove and set at room temperature.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Line muffin tins with cupcake papers. Using wooden spoon, blend the first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl. Carefully fold in the chocolate chips; set aside.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend cream cheese, parsley, chili sauce, onion and hot sauce. Gradually blend in tuna.
Beat until smooth.
Chill in small bowl lined with plastic wrap.
Turn out onto small plate. Surround with crackers.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes and carrots.
Chop onion.
Put carrot, potatoes and onion in pan with 2 1/2 cups water.
Cook until tender.
Put cooked mixture through sieve or vegetable mill.
Add milk to this puree.
Place in double boiler to heat.
Season.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix.
Freeze, then serve 1/2 slush with 1/2 Seven-Up or ginger ale.

title: tropical squares
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally until mixture bubbles. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add Special K cereal and coconut; stir until coated.
Press evenly into bottom of buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let stand in cool place until firm.
Cut in squares.
Add Spanish peanuts to crunchy peanut butter.

title: cinnamon monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon with 1/3 cup sugar; roll biscuits (quartered). Put in a greased pan.
Melt margarine; mix with rest of sugar. Spoon over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: depression casserole
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender.
Stir in ketchup, water, vinegar, mustard and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Place frankfurters in 1-quart baking dish. Pour sauce over.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
If desired, serve over toast points or rice.
Makes 5 servings.

title: fruit blast
directions: Cut melon into bite size pieces; section grapefruit and orange.
Mix all ingredients together,
and chill for 1 hour.

title: ruby slipper cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs in large bowl. Blend, then beat at medium speed 2 minutes until creamy. Spoon 1/3 of batter into well greased and floured 10-inch flute tube pan. Sprinkle 1/2 jello. Repeat layers. Spread remaining batter over jello to cover. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until cake springs back. Remove pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apple muffins
directions: Blend and mix all ingredients.
Pour into small muffin pans. Bake at 325° or 350° for about 7 minutes.

title: life is like a bowl of hash
directions: Mix each day thoroughly with Love and Laughter.
To change the flavor, put in a few Tears; add seven days to make a week.
Turn over enough days to make a month.
Stack 12 months to make a year.
Scramble as many years as possible to make a Life.
It's just like making hash.
Enjoy!

title: ever-ready bran muffins
directions: In a very large bowl, cream the oil and sugar. Add the honey and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Mix good, then add Raisin Bran and mix.

title: fruit slush
directions: Bring to boil the water, sugar and tea bags.
Add lemonade and orange juice.
Freeze.
Fill glass 2/3 with slush; fill with 7-Up or Sprite.

title: italian spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Add celery, green peppers, onion and cucumber.
Add salad dressing and seasoning.
Before serving, add tomatoes and Parmesan cheese.

title: texas cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, put sugar and flour. In saucepan, bring water, oleo, buttermilk, cocoa and shortening to boil.
Pour mixture into flour and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, soda, vanilla and cinnamon; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 20 minutes.
Prepare frosting (recipe follows) and pour over hot cake.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Spread over four slices of meat. Roll first slice, join meat edges to start second slice and continue to roll 4 slices into a log, using remaining slices. Wrap and chill.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Top with olive secured by toothpick.
Place on top of crackers.

title: chocolate mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken breast with mushrooms
directions: This recipe depends on how many servings you need or want.

title: cheese roll
directions: Soften cheese and blend all ingredients.
Shape in a roll and roll in chili powder.
Chill 2 hours.
Slice and serve on Ritz crackers.

title: herring in aquavit sauce(brennevinsild)
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, curry, pepper and aquavit.
Put herring pieces in serving dish; pour sauce over and sprinkle with dill weed.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand 3 hours.
Overnight is better. Good with picnic lunches.

title: church window
directions: In saucepan, combine chips and butter.
Cook and stir on low heat until melted.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in marshmallows and 1/4 cup pecans.
Divide mixture in half.
Shape each half in 6-inch logs.
Roll each in remaining nuts.
Shape on wax paper.
Wrap in wax paper sprinkled with nuts.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: chocolate truffle cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and cocoa until light and fluffy.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls; dip in chocolate sprinkles.
Place sprinkled side up, 2-inches apart, on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until set.
Cool 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Combine the potatoes, onion,
parsley and celery, then mix. In a small bowl, combine the yogurt, mustard and seasoning; add to vegetables and mix carefully.
Cover and chill several hours to allow flavors to blend.

title: sam's potato soup
directions: Put quartered potatoes in a 6-quart pot; just cover potatoes with water; add garlic and boil until cooked, uncovered.
In a frying pan, put oil.
Slice in onions and fry until brown; do not burn.
When potatoes are cooked, save water.
Mash potatoes right in water.
Put stove on medium; add browned onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage and green pepper together.
Drain off grease well. Mix in all other ingredients.
Do not drain.
Bake, covered, for 2 hours at 325°.
Use a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream together all ingredients, except eggs.
Beat the eggs slightly and add to mixture.
Pour into 1 (9-inch) unbaked pie shell.
Put in 350° preheated oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Mix flour, eggs, oil and salt well to form a soft ball.
Let sit covered for about 15 minutes.
Roll thin on floured surface and cut or use a noodle maker.
Drop into boiling water.
Done when the noodles float to the top.
Serve with your favorite recipe.

title: chess cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: dump it cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in the order listed above into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Mix softened butter in crumbs; layer in bottom of pan.
Add layer of chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Drizzle condensed milk over top.
Bake in a 325° or 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cut into desired squares.
Use an 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine jello and crushed pineapple. Heat to dissolve jello. Combine Cool Whip, cottage cheese, jello, pineapple and nuts. Stir well. Add mandarin oranges to top. Refrigerate.

title: liver in soy sauce
directions: Marinate liver in soy sauce and lemon juice.
Pan fry bacon and set aside.
In the bacon fat, saute onions; set aside.
Cook liver in remaining hot fat (about 2 to 3 minutes per side).
When done, add the marinade and garnish
with bacon and onion rings.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine self-rising flour, brown sugar and quick or regular oats.
Add egg, buttermilk, cooking oil, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into muffin tins and cook about 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter and vanilla.
Heat until marshmallows and butter are melted, stirring constantly.
Add food coloring.
Gradually stir in corn flakes.
Drop onto plate to form a wreath.
Decorate with candied cherries (optional).

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn in 1 1/2 pints vinegar.
Twenty minutes after it starts to boil, add other ingredients; cook 20 minutes longer and seal.
This makes 6 quarts.

title: aunt martha riethmiller's lebkuchens
directions: Mix together.
Add some flour.
Mix.
Let stand overnight. In morning, add more flour.
Roll out.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: applesauce pies
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Pour oil and milk into one cup.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until mixed.
Shape into ball. Place dough into ball in between wax paper.
Roll to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut.
Fill with filling; seal.
Use a fork.
Fry 4 to 5 minutes at 350° in 1 inch of oil.
Makes 8 to 10.

title: pistachio dessert salad
directions: Mix pudding in pineapple.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.
(May use sugar-free pudding and light Cool Whip.)

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Saute onion and peppers.
Add to hamburger.
Add tomato sauce and simmer until macaroni is cooked.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Combine sauce and macaroni. Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: sunshine barbecue chicken(makes 4 servings.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in large oven bag; place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add barbecue sauce and orange juice to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Add chicken to bag. Turn bag to coat chicken with sauce.
Arrange chicken in an even layer.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 half-inch slits in top. Bake until chicken is tender, 45 to 50 minutes.
To serve, stir sauce; spoon over chicken.

title: magic brownies
directions: Mix the above ingredients together.
Press in a 13 x 9 cake pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter. In a large bowl, mix butter, squash, milk, cheese, salt, pepper and onion. Pour in a greased casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix sugar with 2 cups warm water and flour.
Add yeast mixture; let set in glass jar covered with a cloth for 5 days.
Put the initial Sourdough Starter in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.
Take out and feed with this mixture: 3/4 cup sugar, 1 cup warm water and 3 tablespoons instant potatoes. Mix well and add to starter.
Let starter stand out of refrigerator all day (8 to 12 hours) or until very bubbly.
Remove 1 cup to make bread and return remaining to the refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator 3 to 5 days and feed again.
If not making bread after feeding starter, throw away 1 cup.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Drain fruit and add to cream cheese mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
If the mixture is too stiff, add 2 tablespoons of fruit juice (your choice). Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together in a bowl the Wesson oil, sugar, eggs, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add flour, then apples and chopped nuts.
Bake slowly about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: short cake
directions: Mix all together (will be stiff).
Bake at 325° until done, about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Layer in large bowl angel food cake (broken in pieces), pudding and
strawberries.	Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle toasted almonds on top.

title: sliced zucchini pickles
directions: Combine zucchini, onion and salt.
Cover with ice and let stand 3 hours.
If needed, add more ice.
Drain thoroughly. Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed, turmeric and mustard in large pan.
Bring to boil.
Add drained vegetables.
Return to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars.
Process in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: "heavenly" banana nut bars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add 2 egg yolks and mix well.
Now add banana pulp.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: In baking dish, place sliced potatoes, carrots and onion. Salt and pepper pork chops.
Place on top of vegetables.
Top with soup.
Add 1/2 can of water. Bake in a 325° oven about 1 1/2 hours.

title: dilled lamb stew
directions: Cut up lamb into 2 inch cubes.
Put meat, salt, dill weed and water in a covered microwaveproof casserole and cook (in microwave) until tender for 25 to 35 minutes, stirring off and on.
Add celery and carrots and cook until tender (5 to 8 minutes). Blend cornstarch and cream.
Stir into stew and continue cooking and stirring until thickened.
Do not overcook meat.
Serves 6.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. Use 2 teaspoons mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: braised veal chops
directions: Rinse and pat dry chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a large skillet or Dutch oven heat oil and lightly brown chops on both sides.
Add carrots, tomatoes and bouillon.
Simmer 45 minutes, covered.
Add mushrooms and sprinkle with parsley.
Cook 5 to 10 more minutes.
Serve veal covered with sauce and veggies. Serves 2.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup of chow mein noodles to use as topping. Combine remainder of noodles, cream of mushroom soup, tuna, celery, onion, nuts, milk and seasoning.
Put in casserole and sprinkle top with remained noodles.
Bake uncovered at 350° preheated oven for 25 minutes.

title: salzburger nockerln(salzburg souffle)
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and creamy; beat in flour.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add vanilla flavored sugar, a little at a time.
The success of the Nockerln depends on the stiffness of the egg whites.
Be sure not to underbeat.

title: creamy custard filling
directions: Combine flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt in a heavy saucepan. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored. Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks. Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in vanilla and butter. Let cool. Yield: about 3 cups.

title: valentine pink salad
directions: Dissolve jell-o in boiling water.
Add frozen berries and stir until thawed.
Add lemon juice.
Mix together mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add a little strawberry mixture and blend; add balance of the strawberry mixture.
Fold in fruit.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: butterscotch pudding pie
directions: Cook pudding mix and milk until mixture reaches a full boil, stirring often.
It will thicken as it cools.
After it cools, pour it in the baked pie shell.
Cover with the marshmallows.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Boil shrimp in shrimp boil and highly seasoned water.
Soften cream cheese with lemon juice and add other ingredients; mix well. Chill at least 8 hours before serving.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Warm in oven at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir every few minutes.

title: scalloped celery
directions: Boil celery, green peppers and onion until tender; drain well. Combine celery mixture, soup and seasoning (salt and pepper to taste) in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
